1
00:02:02,442 --> 00:02:03,477
[Robotnik]
Doctor's log.

2
00:02:03,610 --> 00:02:07,015
It's day 243 in this...

3
00:02:07,148 --> 00:02:09,616
portobello purgatory.

4
00:02:09,750 --> 00:02:12,519
My only companion
is a rock I named Stone.

5
00:02:15,256 --> 00:02:19,160
The question is,
for whom am I narrating this?

6
00:02:19,294 --> 00:02:21,062
[shudders]

7
00:02:21,195 --> 00:02:24,631
<i>It seems I've become</i>
<i>a featured player</i>
<i>in the theater of the absurd.</i>

8
00:02:24,765 --> 00:02:27,802
<i>Marooned in deep space</i>
<i>by that wretched blue rodent.</i>

9
00:02:27,936 --> 00:02:29,670
<i>But it's all good,</i>

10
00:02:29,804 --> 00:02:32,307
<i>thanks to</i>
<i>a breathable atmosphere</i>
<i>and my supreme intellect,</i>

11
00:02:32,439 --> 00:02:35,776
<i>sharpened against</i>
<i>the only competitor</i>
<i>savvy enough to bring it.</i>

12
00:02:35,910 --> 00:02:38,246
Chanterelle to d4.
Mmm.

13
00:02:38,379 --> 00:02:41,648
<i>I've been striving</i>
<i>to make fungi into</i>
<i>a functional drink of choice...</i>

14
00:02:41,782 --> 00:02:43,251
[sniffs]
Mushroom coffee.

15
00:02:43,384 --> 00:02:44,319
[slurps]

16
00:02:44,484 --> 00:02:45,585
[sputters, gags]

17
00:02:45,719 --> 00:02:47,688
<i>...with limited...</i>

18
00:02:48,957 --> 00:02:50,024
<i>limited...</i>

19
00:02:50,158 --> 00:02:51,558
[gags, coughs]

20
00:02:51,692 --> 00:02:53,493
<i>limited...</i>

21
00:02:54,095 --> 00:02:55,529
<i>success.</i>

22
00:02:57,464 --> 00:02:58,532
[gasps]

23
00:02:58,665 --> 00:03:01,269
<i>But today, day 243,</i>

24
00:03:01,402 --> 00:03:04,705
<i>has brought a new optimism</i>
<i>to my most pressing endeavor--</i>

25
00:03:04,839 --> 00:03:09,844
<i>planetus exodus to returnicus</i>
<i>and kick blue butticus.</i>

26
00:03:16,583 --> 00:03:18,219
If my calculations
are correct,

27
00:03:18,353 --> 00:03:22,190
and there's no reason
to say "if"
because they always are...

28
00:03:22,323 --> 00:03:26,593
this quill is going to power
my masterpiece.

29
00:03:28,595 --> 00:03:30,098
Let's light this candle...

30
00:03:31,466 --> 00:03:34,668
and see
who comes a-knockin'.
[electricity crackling]

31
00:03:37,571 --> 00:03:39,007
[shrieks]

32
00:04:40,201 --> 00:04:41,601
Greetings!
[gasps]

33
00:04:45,173 --> 00:04:47,208
[screaming]

34
00:04:47,341 --> 00:04:49,776
<i>Klaatu barada nikto.</i>

35
00:04:51,711 --> 00:04:53,613
[screams]

36
00:04:56,184 --> 00:04:58,853
[weapons humming]

37
00:04:59,854 --> 00:05:01,989
Agent Stone? Now!

38
00:05:05,725 --> 00:05:08,628
[yells, grunts]

39
00:05:11,065 --> 00:05:13,167
[Robotnik]
Thank you, Stone.

40
00:05:14,768 --> 00:05:19,907
It's time
to say goodbye to this
piece-of-shiitake planet!

41
00:05:20,508 --> 00:05:21,675
[grunts]

42
00:05:21,809 --> 00:05:24,212
[panting]

43
00:05:29,283 --> 00:05:31,085
Huh?

44
00:05:44,832 --> 00:05:46,868
Where did you get that?

45
00:05:50,304 --> 00:05:53,274
From a little blue menace
on the planet called Earth.

46
00:05:55,709 --> 00:05:58,112
I'd be happy
to show you the way.

47
00:06:20,835 --> 00:06:22,669
[chuckles] Oh.

48
00:06:22,803 --> 00:06:25,406
[engine racing]

49
00:06:25,540 --> 00:06:28,009
[sirens wailing]

50
00:06:32,679 --> 00:06:34,081
They're still on us.

51
00:06:34,882 --> 00:06:36,551
This'll slow 'em down.
[grunts]

52
00:06:36,683 --> 00:06:38,019
[tires screeching]

53
00:06:49,463 --> 00:06:51,165
["It's Tricky" playing]

54
00:06:51,299 --> 00:06:54,402
♪ <i>This speech is my recital</i>
<i>I think it's very vital</i> ♪

55
00:06:54,535 --> 00:06:56,137
♪ <i>To rock a rhyme</i>
<i>That's right on time</i> ♪

56
00:06:56,270 --> 00:06:58,306
♪ <i>"It's Tricky" is the title</i>
<i>Here we go</i> ♪

57
00:06:58,439 --> 00:07:00,675
♪ <i>It's tricky to rock a rhyme</i>
<i>To rock a rhyme</i> ♪

58
00:07:00,808 --> 00:07:02,310
♪ <i>That's right on time</i>
<i>It's tricky</i> ♪

59
00:07:02,443 --> 00:07:04,711
Watch out. Excuse me.
Pardon me. Coming through.

60
00:07:04,845 --> 00:07:06,280
[song continues playing]

61
00:07:06,414 --> 00:07:08,449
Good evening, gentlemen.
Mind if I drive?

62
00:07:08,583 --> 00:07:10,784
[tires squealing]
[screaming]

63
00:07:10,918 --> 00:07:12,453
Better buckle up.

64
00:07:13,955 --> 00:07:16,023
[robbers screaming]

65
00:07:19,994 --> 00:07:22,063
How we doing back there?

66
00:07:22,830 --> 00:07:24,398
And now this way.

67
00:07:24,532 --> 00:07:25,499
[grunting]

68
00:07:25,633 --> 00:07:27,134
[Sonic laughing]

69
00:07:27,702 --> 00:07:30,037
Whoo-hoo!

70
00:07:30,471 --> 00:07:33,107
[muffled shouting]

71
00:07:33,241 --> 00:07:35,409
Oh, I'm sorry.
I don't speak duct tape.

72
00:07:35,543 --> 00:07:36,677
[grunts]

73
00:07:36,811 --> 00:07:38,946
What the heck are you?
Fear not, citizen.

74
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:43,017
I am the hero you need
and the hero you deserve.

75
00:07:43,150 --> 00:07:45,653
The blue dawn
that banishes the darkest--

76
00:07:45,785 --> 00:07:47,388
Holy crap!

77
00:07:47,521 --> 00:07:48,456
[both screaming]

78
00:07:48,589 --> 00:07:50,625
[tires squealing]

79
00:07:50,757 --> 00:07:51,926
[screaming]
Don't worry.

80
00:07:52,059 --> 00:07:53,961
Nobody's gonna get hurt.

81
00:07:58,366 --> 00:08:00,568
Huh.
What are those?
Bombs. Bombs.

82
00:08:00,701 --> 00:08:01,936
They're bombs!
Those are bombs!

83
00:08:02,069 --> 00:08:04,138
Relax.
They're not even lit.

84
00:08:04,272 --> 00:08:08,042
So I'll say again,
nobody's gonna get--

85
00:08:08,175 --> 00:08:11,045
[screams] I was wrong!
We're all gonna die!
[whimpering]

86
00:08:13,281 --> 00:08:14,715
Why aren't you slowing down?

87
00:08:14,849 --> 00:08:16,884
That would require brakes.

88
00:08:18,219 --> 00:08:21,188
Oh, it's hot.
Hot, hot, hot!

89
00:08:21,322 --> 00:08:23,024
Why don't you just let
the police handle this?

90
00:08:23,157 --> 00:08:26,360
Because that's not
what heroes do.

91
00:08:29,063 --> 00:08:32,333
Thank you very much.
Please hold your applause.

92
00:08:33,601 --> 00:08:35,202
[horns honking]

93
00:08:35,336 --> 00:08:36,337
[fuse sizzling]

94
00:08:36,470 --> 00:08:39,373
Do you hear that?
There's one bomb left.

95
00:08:39,507 --> 00:08:41,642
Uh... Uh-oh.

96
00:08:41,776 --> 00:08:42,943
Did you check
under the seat?

97
00:08:43,077 --> 00:08:44,879
Of course I checked
under the seat!

98
00:08:45,012 --> 00:08:46,113
[horn honking]

99
00:08:46,247 --> 00:08:47,748
You are terrible at this!

100
00:08:47,882 --> 00:08:50,885
You know what?
Your negative attitude
is not helping anyone.

101
00:08:51,018 --> 00:08:53,220
It's in your spiky things!

102
00:08:54,255 --> 00:08:57,558
Ha! I can never
find anything in here.
[grunts]

103
00:08:58,459 --> 00:09:01,729
Drained it from downtown!
[mimics fanfare]

104
00:09:01,862 --> 00:09:04,465
See? I told you
nobody would get hurt.

105
00:09:04,999 --> 00:09:06,767
[people chattering]

106
00:09:06,901 --> 00:09:08,969
Holy sherbet!

107
00:09:10,806 --> 00:09:11,906
Oh, hello.

108
00:09:12,039 --> 00:09:15,009
Don't panic.
This is only a drill.

109
00:09:15,710 --> 00:09:18,579
[drill whirring]

110
00:09:18,713 --> 00:09:20,081
[people exclaiming]

111
00:09:25,486 --> 00:09:29,223
[guard screaming]

112
00:09:30,791 --> 00:09:33,127
[breathing shakily]

113
00:09:39,767 --> 00:09:41,001
[fuse sizzling]

114
00:09:42,870 --> 00:09:44,105
[gasps]

115
00:09:54,048 --> 00:09:56,350
[sirens wailing]
[tires screech]

116
00:09:56,951 --> 00:09:57,985
Come here!

117
00:09:58,119 --> 00:10:00,822
No need to thank me, citizens.

118
00:10:00,955 --> 00:10:03,791
All in a night's work for...

119
00:10:03,924 --> 00:10:06,527
Blue Justice!

120
00:10:06,660 --> 00:10:08,429
You're a terrible hero!

121
00:10:08,562 --> 00:10:10,965
[Sonic laughing]

122
00:10:11,098 --> 00:10:12,266
["Stars In The Sky" playing]

123
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:14,836
♪ <i>The feelings running deep</i> ♪

124
00:10:14,969 --> 00:10:16,604
♪ <i>Ain't no time for sleep</i> ♪

125
00:10:16,737 --> 00:10:20,107
♪ <i>A second to unwind</i>
<i>Head up in the sky</i> ♪

126
00:10:20,241 --> 00:10:21,375
[Sonic] Morning, Wade!

127
00:10:21,509 --> 00:10:22,543
Morning, Sonic!

128
00:10:22,676 --> 00:10:26,480
[song continues playing]

129
00:10:27,348 --> 00:10:30,050
[Sonic] Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

130
00:10:30,184 --> 00:10:33,220
Good morning, Green Hills!

131
00:10:42,062 --> 00:10:42,997
[grunting]

132
00:10:43,130 --> 00:10:45,332
Ah! Oop! Oh.

133
00:10:45,466 --> 00:10:47,301
[sighs]

134
00:10:47,435 --> 00:10:50,872
[floor creaking]
[groaning]

135
00:10:51,005 --> 00:10:53,274
[floor creaks louder]
Oh, come on.

136
00:10:54,742 --> 00:10:57,178
Uh-oh. Uh...

137
00:11:03,751 --> 00:11:05,152
[gasps]

138
00:11:14,428 --> 00:11:15,429
[inaudible]

139
00:11:15,563 --> 00:11:17,031
Oh, Sonic.

140
00:11:17,164 --> 00:11:19,099
I miss you, Longclaw.

141
00:11:19,967 --> 00:11:21,669
I'm trying
to make you proud.

142
00:11:30,077 --> 00:11:34,748
[yawning] And now
for a little shut-eye.

143
00:11:36,183 --> 00:11:37,318
[lapping]

144
00:11:37,451 --> 00:11:38,719
Oh! Blech!

145
00:11:38,854 --> 00:11:40,354
Ozzy, morning breath!

146
00:11:40,488 --> 00:11:42,356
Sonic.
Are you still in bed?

147
00:11:42,490 --> 00:11:44,992
You're supposed
to meet Tom, remember?

148
00:11:45,125 --> 00:11:46,494
[grunts]

149
00:11:46,627 --> 00:11:50,531
All right, all right,
I'm up! I'm up.

150
00:11:51,198 --> 00:11:53,334
[Tom sighs]
What a day.

151
00:11:53,767 --> 00:11:55,636
Whoo!

152
00:11:55,769 --> 00:11:57,806
Thanks for coming out, bud.

153
00:11:57,939 --> 00:11:59,340
You know,
I feel like you and me,

154
00:11:59,473 --> 00:12:01,642
we haven't had
much time together lately.

155
00:12:03,845 --> 00:12:06,080
How's it going over there?
You getting any bites?

156
00:12:06,213 --> 00:12:08,682
[snoring]

157
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:15,489
[screams]
I can't swim! Help!

158
00:12:15,623 --> 00:12:17,758
If I die,
don't look in my closet!

159
00:12:17,893 --> 00:12:20,127
Hey, hey, you're good.
You're all right. Come on.

160
00:12:20,261 --> 00:12:21,462
[shivering]
It's freezing.

161
00:12:21,595 --> 00:12:23,899
All right, okay.
Take it easy.

162
00:12:24,031 --> 00:12:25,299
[shivering]

163
00:12:25,432 --> 00:12:28,035
All right.
You're good. Okay.

164
00:12:31,472 --> 00:12:34,108
But now that you've had
a nap and a bath...

165
00:12:34,241 --> 00:12:38,712
<i>I went up to your room</i>
<i>last night to bring you</i>
<i>some new comics and, um...</i>

166
00:12:42,918 --> 00:12:44,853
[Sonic on tape]
<i>Whoa, whoa, whoa.</i>
<i>Stop right there.</i>

167
00:12:44,986 --> 00:12:46,387
<i>I wouldn't come any closer,</i>

168
00:12:46,520 --> 00:12:48,957
<i>because this little hedgehog</i>
<i>had way too many chili dogs.</i>

169
00:12:49,089 --> 00:12:50,724
<i>Oh, no. Oh, no.</i> [farts]

170
00:12:50,859 --> 00:12:53,127
<i>I'm so embarrassed.</i>
<i>Get out of here quick!</i>

171
00:12:53,260 --> 00:12:55,596
<i>Oh, no, here comes another one!</i>
[farts]

172
00:12:55,729 --> 00:12:57,498
<i>Go. Now. Save yourself.</i>

173
00:12:57,631 --> 00:13:00,100
[tape rewinds] <i>Whoa, whoa, whoa.</i>
<i>Stop right there.</i>
<i>I wouldn't come any closer,</i>

174
00:13:00,234 --> 00:13:03,437
[distorting]
<i>because this little hedgehog</i>
<i>had way too many chili dogs.</i>

175
00:13:03,571 --> 00:13:05,372
<i>Oh, no. Oh, no.</i>
[farts]

176
00:13:05,506 --> 00:13:07,241
<i>I'm so embarrassed.</i>
<i>Get out of here--</i>

177
00:13:07,374 --> 00:13:09,743
Ugh! I knew I should've
used real farts.

178
00:13:12,580 --> 00:13:14,214
How many times
are we gonna do this?

179
00:13:14,348 --> 00:13:16,750
What? Cast your line
and not catch anything?
Seems like a billion.

180
00:13:16,885 --> 00:13:19,320
I think you know
what I'm talking about.

181
00:13:19,453 --> 00:13:21,856
The lying.
The sneaking out.

182
00:13:21,990 --> 00:13:23,257
The pretending
to be Batman.

183
00:13:23,390 --> 00:13:24,993
Blue Justice,
trademark pending.

184
00:13:25,125 --> 00:13:26,226
Whatever.
You're being reckless.

185
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:28,462
Ugh!
Not this conversation again.

186
00:13:28,596 --> 00:13:30,264
Hey. It's no fun
for me, either.

187
00:13:30,397 --> 00:13:31,665
But if you keep
being irresponsible,

188
00:13:31,799 --> 00:13:33,400
we're gonna keep
having this conversation.

189
00:13:33,534 --> 00:13:35,302
How is it irresponsible
to use my powers?

190
00:13:35,436 --> 00:13:38,405
Sonic, you destroyed
an entire city block!

191
00:13:38,539 --> 00:13:40,140
That block
was already messed up.

192
00:13:40,274 --> 00:13:41,408
Who cares?

193
00:13:41,542 --> 00:13:44,913
Look, I stopped a robbery.
I was a hero.

194
00:13:45,046 --> 00:13:48,415
No, you put people
in danger and that's not
what a hero does.

195
00:13:50,551 --> 00:13:53,721
[sighs] You're supposed
to be my friend.

196
00:13:53,855 --> 00:13:55,389
Stop trying to be my dad.

197
00:13:56,657 --> 00:13:57,892
[sighs]

198
00:14:00,194 --> 00:14:02,030
I can take care of myself.

199
00:14:02,162 --> 00:14:04,465
Sonic,
taking care of yourself

200
00:14:04,598 --> 00:14:06,567
is not what being
a hero's all about.

201
00:14:06,700 --> 00:14:09,370
It's about
taking responsibility
for other people.

202
00:14:09,503 --> 00:14:11,940
And right now,
whether you want
to hear this or not,

203
00:14:12,073 --> 00:14:13,240
you are still just a kid.

204
00:14:13,374 --> 00:14:15,542
You got some more
growing up to do

205
00:14:15,676 --> 00:14:17,879
before you're ready
to be the big hero.

206
00:14:18,612 --> 00:14:20,048
But trust me
when I tell you,

207
00:14:20,180 --> 00:14:22,851
there will come a time
when your powers
will be needed.

208
00:14:24,518 --> 00:14:27,388
But you don't choose
that moment.

209
00:14:27,521 --> 00:14:29,223
That moment chooses you.

210
00:14:29,356 --> 00:14:32,226
Whoa. Look at you.
[chuckles]

211
00:14:32,359 --> 00:14:35,096
Look at that.
I just got goose bumps.

212
00:14:35,229 --> 00:14:36,764
Wait a second.
Did you steal that from Oprah?

213
00:14:36,898 --> 00:14:40,068
No, sir. That is
a Wachowski family special.

214
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:41,635
Came from my dad,

215
00:14:41,769 --> 00:14:44,105
in this very boat,
on this very lake.

216
00:14:45,205 --> 00:14:48,275
He would always try and steer me
in the right direction.

217
00:14:48,409 --> 00:14:50,945
And that's what Maddie and I
have always tried to do
with you.

218
00:14:52,113 --> 00:14:55,984
So, until
your moment arrives,

219
00:14:56,117 --> 00:14:58,887
I want you to work on
being a little more responsible.

220
00:15:00,220 --> 00:15:01,522
<i>Comprende?</i>

221
00:15:02,123 --> 00:15:03,557
<i>Comprende.</i>

222
00:15:04,159 --> 00:15:05,894
High five on it.

223
00:15:06,027 --> 00:15:09,697
Yeah! Donut Lord
and the Blue Blur
are back at it again!

224
00:15:09,831 --> 00:15:11,265
Hang on.

225
00:15:11,398 --> 00:15:12,433
Speedboat!

226
00:15:12,566 --> 00:15:14,535
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

227
00:15:15,769 --> 00:15:17,337
[Sonic laughing]
[Tom] Sonic!

228
00:15:17,471 --> 00:15:19,740
[Sonic] Whoo-hoo!

229
00:15:19,874 --> 00:15:23,812
How excited are you,
going to Hawaii with me?
Oh, Hawaii.

230
00:15:23,945 --> 00:15:25,980
Oh, yeah!
[chuckles]

231
00:15:26,981 --> 00:15:28,482
Wow.
[laughs]

232
00:15:28,615 --> 00:15:31,652
Welcome to Sonic Air,
the fastest way to travel.

233
00:15:31,785 --> 00:15:33,220
Now boarding groups
one and two.

234
00:15:33,353 --> 00:15:35,789
[laughs] Oh!

235
00:15:35,924 --> 00:15:38,093
Sonic, this is so fun!

236
00:15:38,225 --> 00:15:40,561
I'm sorry, ma'am,
you're group three.
Please wait your turn.

237
00:15:40,694 --> 00:15:42,396
Anyone from groups
one and two?

238
00:15:42,529 --> 00:15:44,231
Just let him
get it out of his system.
Nobody?

239
00:15:44,364 --> 00:15:46,700
Okay, then everybody else
right this way.

240
00:15:46,835 --> 00:15:47,701
Thank you.

241
00:15:47,836 --> 00:15:51,840
[imitating
electronic scanner noises]

242
00:15:51,973 --> 00:15:53,108
[laughs]

243
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:55,944
And you, sir?
[imitating scanner]

244
00:15:56,077 --> 00:15:57,344
