487
00:27:13,621 --> 00:27:15,891
I've got an idea.
Do you trust me?

488
00:27:16,023 --> 00:27:18,125
Of course not!
I literally just met you!

489
00:27:18,259 --> 00:27:20,461
Just let me-- Come on!
What are you doing?

490
00:27:20,594 --> 00:27:22,696
[Sonic screaming]

491
00:27:24,965 --> 00:27:27,401
[screaming continues]

492
00:27:31,539 --> 00:27:33,040
[grunts]

493
00:27:34,575 --> 00:27:37,144
[whimpering]

494
00:27:39,513 --> 00:27:40,548
We're flying.

495
00:27:40,681 --> 00:27:43,250
Uh, did your butt just
turn into a helicopter?

496
00:27:43,384 --> 00:27:46,053
[laughs] A butt-copter!

497
00:27:46,187 --> 00:27:50,524
Oh, only Sonic the Hedgehog
could come up with
something like that.

498
00:27:51,860 --> 00:27:54,962
[tractor engine
sputters, dies]

499
00:27:56,497 --> 00:27:58,732
[grunts]
[tractor hissing]

500
00:28:03,103 --> 00:28:07,575
[chuckles]
Foxy move.

501
00:28:08,910 --> 00:28:10,778
You want something
done right...

502
00:28:10,912 --> 00:28:12,179
[electronic beeping]

503
00:28:12,313 --> 00:28:15,416
...you have to hire someone
you can push around.

504
00:28:17,518 --> 00:28:18,252
All caps.

505
00:28:18,385 --> 00:28:20,287
["Don't Know Why" playing]

506
00:28:20,421 --> 00:28:22,056
[whirring]

507
00:28:28,362 --> 00:28:34,535
♪ <i>I waited till I saw the sun</i> ♪

508
00:28:34,668 --> 00:28:36,570
♪ <i>I don't know why</i>
<i>I didn't come</i> ♪

509
00:28:36,704 --> 00:28:38,172
Doctor,

510
00:28:38,874 --> 00:28:40,174
where are you?

511
00:28:40,307 --> 00:28:43,043
[song continues playing]

512
00:28:43,177 --> 00:28:45,145
[slams utensil on counter]

513
00:28:46,815 --> 00:28:48,082
Freak.

514
00:28:50,184 --> 00:28:51,652
[sighs]

515
00:28:51,785 --> 00:28:53,087
[watch chimes]

516
00:28:55,422 --> 00:28:57,893
Oh, I, uh--
I'm sorry, folks.

517
00:28:58,025 --> 00:29:00,594
Uh, I have to close early.
Everybody out!

518
00:29:00,728 --> 00:29:03,932
Everybody out.
Thank you for visiting
the Mean Bean.

519
00:29:04,064 --> 00:29:06,333
All right, good night.
Good night.

520
00:29:12,941 --> 00:29:14,642
[electronic whirring]

521
00:29:14,775 --> 00:29:17,611
[scanner trilling]

522
00:29:25,252 --> 00:29:26,520
He's back.

523
00:29:28,055 --> 00:29:30,624
He's back!

524
00:30:06,327 --> 00:30:08,395
[drones humming]

525
00:30:15,302 --> 00:30:18,105
[inhales, exhales]

526
00:30:24,879 --> 00:30:27,281
That's more like it.

527
00:30:28,049 --> 00:30:31,151
I've been re-hatched!

528
00:30:33,654 --> 00:30:36,223
[grunting]

529
00:30:36,825 --> 00:30:37,859
[gasps]

530
00:30:39,293 --> 00:30:41,428
[growls]

531
00:30:42,363 --> 00:30:46,935
So, my massively
metacarpaled friend,

532
00:30:47,068 --> 00:30:50,105
you mentioned...
[howling]

533
00:30:50,237 --> 00:30:52,172
...ultimate power.

534
00:30:52,306 --> 00:30:53,240
Back at the house?

535
00:30:53,374 --> 00:30:55,010
The Master Emerald?

536
00:30:55,142 --> 00:30:56,677
It does not concern you.

537
00:30:56,811 --> 00:30:59,446
I got you off that planet
and you brought me
to the hedgehog.

538
00:30:59,580 --> 00:31:01,582
We have no more use
for each other.

539
00:31:01,715 --> 00:31:03,918
Well, I hate to be
a contrarian, but...

540
00:31:04,052 --> 00:31:04,986
[gloves beep]

541
00:31:05,120 --> 00:31:06,453
...I think we might.

542
00:31:07,655 --> 00:31:09,924
You think these machines
are a match for me?

543
00:31:10,058 --> 00:31:13,761
I will shatter them
like the bones from a fallen--

544
00:31:13,895 --> 00:31:15,864
Oh, they are stairs.

545
00:31:21,402 --> 00:31:25,807
You see,
Earth is my turf, G.

546
00:31:25,940 --> 00:31:28,676
If you don't know
how to floss,
you'll be lost without me.

547
00:31:28,810 --> 00:31:31,378
I understand nothing
of what you just said.

548
00:31:31,512 --> 00:31:36,250
I help you
retrieve the Emerald,
and you use it to...

549
00:31:37,251 --> 00:31:42,289
destroy the hedgehog!

550
00:31:42,423 --> 00:31:44,525
You're suggesting
an alliance.

551
00:31:44,658 --> 00:31:48,997
Around here we simply
grip each other's hands tightly.

552
00:31:49,864 --> 00:31:52,633
[bones cracking]
Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow!

553
00:31:52,766 --> 00:31:54,135
[gasping]

554
00:31:54,268 --> 00:31:57,705
You truculent
space bumpkin!

555
00:31:57,839 --> 00:32:00,108
You've crushed
my favorite hand!

556
00:32:00,240 --> 00:32:02,776
Really?
My hand is uninjured.

557
00:32:02,911 --> 00:32:03,945
Ugh.

558
00:32:04,079 --> 00:32:06,147
But I'm now convinced
of your commitment.

559
00:32:06,280 --> 00:32:07,949
"Oh, goody,"

560
00:32:08,083 --> 00:32:11,820
he exclaimed,
while he reset
two of his knuckles.

561
00:32:11,953 --> 00:32:14,155
[bones crack]
I'm...

562
00:32:14,321 --> 00:32:19,460
delighted to be
on the same team.

563
00:32:27,168 --> 00:32:28,736
Road trip!

564
00:32:28,870 --> 00:32:31,705
I'll let you
stick your nose
out the window.

565
00:32:32,573 --> 00:32:35,009
[Tails]
Uh, Sonic, where are we?

566
00:32:35,143 --> 00:32:37,377
Welcome to
the Wade Cave.

567
00:32:37,511 --> 00:32:40,481
Which is something I hope
to someday say to a woman.

568
00:32:40,614 --> 00:32:42,282
A woman who's not my mom.
[chuckles]

569
00:32:42,416 --> 00:32:44,318
Wade, focus.

570
00:32:44,451 --> 00:32:45,954
We need to figure out
why Knuckles thinks

571
00:32:46,087 --> 00:32:48,156
I'm the key to finding
the Master Emerald.

572
00:32:48,288 --> 00:32:50,557
And why did
he mention Longclaw?

573
00:32:50,691 --> 00:32:53,027
There must be a connection.

574
00:32:53,161 --> 00:32:55,163
Wait a minute.
There is.

575
00:32:55,295 --> 00:32:59,399
Look.
There's an emerald symbol
on the map Longclaw gave me.

576
00:32:59,533 --> 00:33:02,070
I never knew
what it meant before.

577
00:33:02,203 --> 00:33:03,670
[Tails]
Something's happening.

578
00:33:03,805 --> 00:33:06,875
Whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa!

579
00:33:17,051 --> 00:33:18,285
Longclaw?

580
00:33:18,418 --> 00:33:20,021
Hello, Sonic.

581
00:33:20,155 --> 00:33:23,357
If you're watching this,
then something has
happened to me.

582
00:33:23,490 --> 00:33:26,627
And I pray you've made it
to Earth unharmed.

583
00:33:26,760 --> 00:33:30,932
This world has been chosen
for a very important reason.

584
00:33:31,065 --> 00:33:35,236
It's the secret location
of the Master Emerald.

585
00:33:35,369 --> 00:33:36,838
Whoa.

586
00:33:36,971 --> 00:33:40,842
The Emerald has the power
to turn thoughts
into reality.

587
00:33:40,975 --> 00:33:43,710
Like the
Stay Puft Marshmallow Man
from <i>Ghostbusters.</i>

588
00:33:43,845 --> 00:33:44,846
Shh!

589
00:33:44,979 --> 00:33:45,980
In the wrong hands,

590
00:33:46,114 --> 00:33:48,382
it could threaten
all life in the universe.

591
00:33:48,515 --> 00:33:51,385
Protecting the Emerald
was my sacred duty.

592
00:33:51,518 --> 00:33:55,489
And now I must pass
that responsibility to you.

593
00:33:56,356 --> 00:33:58,827
This is my moment.

594
00:33:58,960 --> 00:34:02,729
Follow the map,
find the Emerald,
and keep it safe.

595
00:34:03,231 --> 00:34:04,631
My dear Sonic,

596
00:34:04,765 --> 00:34:08,269
you have a heart
like no creature
I've ever known.

597
00:34:08,402 --> 00:34:10,370
I love you so much.

598
00:34:11,873 --> 00:34:13,074
Goodbye.

599
00:34:14,341 --> 00:34:17,045
No, no, wait.
[sighs]

600
00:34:23,284 --> 00:34:25,419
I won't let you down,
Longclaw.

601
00:34:27,155 --> 00:34:30,191
So is that
y-your dad?

602
00:34:30,325 --> 00:34:31,826
What?

603
00:34:31,960 --> 00:34:32,894
No?

604
00:34:33,027 --> 00:34:34,528
According to this map,

605
00:34:34,661 --> 00:34:36,164
the first clue
is in Siberia.

606
00:34:36,297 --> 00:34:38,665
It's a compass
that will lead
to the Emerald.

607
00:34:38,799 --> 00:34:41,870
And with Knuckles
already here,
it's a race.

608
00:34:42,003 --> 00:34:43,470
Knuckles?

609
00:34:43,604 --> 00:34:45,372
I knew a kid
in middle school
named Knuckles.

610
00:34:45,505 --> 00:34:47,308
Could fit his whole fist
in his mouth.

611
00:34:47,441 --> 00:34:49,310
If this is
the same Knuckles...

612
00:34:49,443 --> 00:34:51,279
[exhales]
...we are screwed.

613
00:34:51,411 --> 00:34:54,082
This Knuckles,
that Knuckles.
It doesn't matter.

614
00:34:54,215 --> 00:34:55,984
We're gonna get there first.

615
00:34:57,252 --> 00:34:58,619
[chuckles]

616
00:34:58,752 --> 00:35:00,487
What do you mean, "we"?

617
00:35:00,621 --> 00:35:01,990
You're coming with me.

618
00:35:02,123 --> 00:35:03,490
Oh, no, no, no.

619
00:35:03,624 --> 00:35:06,560
I just came here to warn you.
I'm not a field guy.

620
00:35:06,693 --> 00:35:08,395
Don't worry.
I got your back.

621
00:35:08,528 --> 00:35:10,764
I won't let anything
happen to you.

622
00:35:12,100 --> 00:35:13,067
It's a power bump.

623
00:35:13,201 --> 00:35:15,837
On Earth, it means
an unbreakable promise.

624
00:35:15,970 --> 00:35:18,772
Okay, I'm in.

625
00:35:19,406 --> 00:35:21,175
["Me and You" playing]

626
00:35:21,309 --> 00:35:25,980
♪ <i>Me and you</i>
<i>Maybe sunshine, maybe rain</i> ♪

627
00:35:34,322 --> 00:35:36,858
Doctor.
It's really you.

628
00:35:37,557 --> 00:35:39,559
You look different.

629
00:35:39,693 --> 00:35:42,663
Papa's got
a brand new 'stache.

630
00:35:43,364 --> 00:35:44,598
Ha!

631
00:35:45,532 --> 00:35:47,168
I knew it. I knew it!

632
00:35:47,302 --> 00:35:48,970
I knew you'd come back, sir.

633
00:35:49,103 --> 00:35:52,539
I never stopped steaming
your Austrian goat's milk.

634
00:35:55,276 --> 00:35:56,777
[Robotnik smacks lips]

635
00:35:57,577 --> 00:35:59,080
Could use some mushroom.

636
00:36:00,747 --> 00:36:01,816
You brought something.

637
00:36:01,950 --> 00:36:05,786
Some kind of, uh,
space porcupine.

638
00:36:05,920 --> 00:36:08,890
Porcupine?
I am an Echidna!

639
00:36:09,023 --> 00:36:11,591
Trained since birth
in all forms
of lethal combat,

640
00:36:11,725 --> 00:36:13,828
destined to restore honor
to my tribe,

641
00:36:13,962 --> 00:36:18,032
and willing to destroy
anything that gets in my way.

642
00:36:18,498 --> 00:36:19,733
Welcome to the team.

643
00:36:19,867 --> 00:36:22,103
[bones cracking]
[groaning]

644
00:36:22,236 --> 00:36:25,840
[gasping]
[laughing]

645
00:36:25,974 --> 00:36:28,475
That means
he trusts you, Stone.

646
00:36:28,608 --> 00:36:31,312
Now let's renovate
this dump!

647
00:36:31,446 --> 00:36:34,614
Latte with steamed
Austrian goat milk!

648
00:36:35,615 --> 00:36:38,585
[machinery whirring]

649
00:36:51,798 --> 00:36:53,633
[grunts]
[players cheering]

650
00:36:54,634 --> 00:36:56,070
Good one. Solid.

651
00:36:57,271 --> 00:36:59,807
[grunting]

652
00:36:59,941 --> 00:37:02,609
[players laughing, cheering]

653
00:37:02,743 --> 00:37:04,212
Sorry, fellas.
[player] That's game!

654
00:37:04,345 --> 00:37:07,215
Ha! That's how we do!
That's how we do!

655
00:37:07,348 --> 00:37:08,449
But are they good at math?

656
00:37:08,582 --> 00:37:10,650
[player]
Teamwork makes the dream work!

657
00:37:10,784 --> 00:37:12,586
Sorry about that,
Big Tom.

658
00:37:12,719 --> 00:37:14,489
Are you good?
All good. Fine.

659
00:37:14,654 --> 00:37:17,791
Thanks for inviting me
out to hang with you
and your groomsmen.

660
00:37:17,925 --> 00:37:19,994
Good quality bonding.

661
00:37:20,128 --> 00:37:21,528
You know, bro,

662
00:37:21,661 --> 00:37:23,730
those guys right there,
they're way more
than my groomsmen.

663
00:37:23,865 --> 00:37:25,266
That's my squad.

664
00:37:25,400 --> 00:37:27,235
Never would've made it
through life without 'em.

665
00:37:27,368 --> 00:37:28,469
Get over here!

666
00:37:28,602 --> 00:37:30,171
Yeah, I'm coming!
I'm coming!

667
00:37:30,304 --> 00:37:31,506
I'll catch you later.

668
00:37:31,638 --> 00:37:33,207
Hey. Yeah!

669
00:37:33,341 --> 00:37:35,709
Let me know if you're ready
for some power yoga, huh?

670
00:37:35,843 --> 00:37:38,813
You bet.
Come on, Tommy boy.
Let's go.

671
00:37:38,946 --> 00:37:41,115
Don't make me.
[laughs]

672
00:37:41,249 --> 00:37:42,250
What am I doing?

673
00:37:42,383 --> 00:37:43,550
Hey, Uncle Tommy!

674
00:37:43,683 --> 00:37:45,219
Hey, girls!

675
00:37:45,353 --> 00:37:46,487
How you do-- Oh!

676
00:37:46,620 --> 00:37:48,156
Are those
the wedding rings?
Uh-huh.

677
00:37:48,289 --> 00:37:49,891
May I?

678
00:37:50,024 --> 00:37:52,659
This little ring bearer
has been taking her job
very seriously.

679
00:37:52,793 --> 00:37:54,362
She's been practicing
all morning.

680
00:37:54,495 --> 00:37:55,595
I can see that.

681
00:37:55,729 --> 00:37:57,965
How very responsible of you.

682
00:37:58,099 --> 00:38:00,401
Except aren't there supposed
to be two wedding rings?

683
00:38:00,535 --> 00:38:02,437
Uh-oh.

684
00:38:02,569 --> 00:38:03,603
Uncle Tommy?

685
00:38:03,737 --> 00:38:06,606
Hang on.
What's going on here?

686
00:38:08,708 --> 00:38:10,011
You're gonna do great,
kiddo.

687
00:38:10,144 --> 00:38:11,112
Bye.

688
00:38:11,245 --> 00:38:12,746
Hey, baby.
Hi.

689
00:38:13,548 --> 00:38:14,949
[groomsmen cheering]
[cork pops]

690
00:38:15,083 --> 00:38:17,584
That's right!
Groom in the building!

691
00:38:17,717 --> 00:38:19,220
Look at those guys.

692
00:38:19,353 --> 00:38:21,621
I wish Sonic had that.

693
00:38:21,755 --> 00:38:23,891
Muscles?
Control yourself.

694
00:38:24,025 --> 00:38:24,826
Mm-hmm.

695
00:38:24,959 --> 00:38:28,396
No. Buddies.
Wingmen. A squad.

696
00:38:28,529 --> 00:38:32,366
Sonic doesn't have
anything like that.
He's flying solo.

697
00:38:33,034 --> 00:38:34,936
Baby, you got to relax.

698
00:38:35,069 --> 00:38:37,171
You're at
the Four Seasons.

699
00:38:37,305 --> 00:38:40,174
Have a mai tai.
Spend some time
with your wife.

700
00:38:40,308 --> 00:38:43,511
That's what he said.
Seriously, his exact words.

701
00:38:43,643 --> 00:38:45,645
See?
He's a smart kid.
All right.

702
00:38:45,779 --> 00:38:47,415
Hmm.
He'll find his way.

703
00:38:47,548 --> 00:38:51,152
I absolutely cannot
find my way.
[wind howling]

704
00:38:51,285 --> 00:38:54,721
We are completely, totally,
unequivocally lost.

705
00:38:54,856 --> 00:38:56,190
[device beeping]

706
00:38:56,324 --> 00:38:57,691
Sonic, in this weather,

707
00:38:57,825 --> 00:39:00,528
there's no way we're gonna get
any readings on this thing!

708
00:39:00,660 --> 00:39:01,829
Should we go back?

709
00:39:01,963 --> 00:39:03,797
No, no, no.
There's a light up ahead.

710
00:39:03,931 --> 00:39:06,134
Maybe we can take shelter
in there.

711
00:39:09,804 --> 00:39:12,340
Ah. Perfect.

712
00:39:12,473 --> 00:39:15,543
Are you sure about this?
We don't know who's inside.

713
00:39:15,675 --> 00:39:19,013
Don't worry.
On Earth, people are
very welcoming,

714
00:39:19,147 --> 00:39:22,517
and love taking
complete strangers
into their homes.

715
00:39:22,649 --> 00:39:26,420
[people chattering in Russian]
[up-tempo music playing]

716
00:39:29,557 --> 00:39:31,993
[door creaks open]

717
00:39:32,126 --> 00:39:34,761
[music and chatter stops]

718
00:39:38,266 --> 00:39:40,001
[both gasp]

719
00:39:41,502 --> 00:39:42,904
[both gasp]

720
00:39:44,405 --> 00:39:45,907
[both sigh]

721
00:39:48,442 --> 00:39:49,577
[both scream]

722
00:39:49,709 --> 00:39:51,245
[grunts]

723
00:39:52,746 --> 00:39:54,015
Run.

724
00:39:54,515 --> 00:39:56,317
[groans]

725
00:39:56,450 --> 00:39:58,186
Table for two, please!

726
00:39:59,786 --> 00:40:02,356
[speaking Russian]

727
00:40:02,490 --> 00:40:03,991
Two beef stews, please.

728
00:40:04,125 --> 00:40:06,294
[translating into Russian]

729
00:40:09,430 --> 00:40:11,232
Where'd you get
all these cool gadgets?

730
00:40:11,365 --> 00:40:12,667
I invented 'em.

731
00:40:12,799 --> 00:40:14,701
That's kinda my thing.

732
00:40:14,835 --> 00:40:17,939
In fact, my inventions
are how I discovered you.

733
00:40:18,072 --> 00:40:20,274
<i>Remember that night</i>
<i>at the baseball field?</i>

734
00:40:20,408 --> 00:40:24,111
<i>Your energy blast</i>
<i>reached all the way</i>
<i>to my home planet.</i>

735
00:40:24,245 --> 00:40:28,883
I saw you save
your whole village
from that crazy mustache guy.

736
00:40:29,016 --> 00:40:32,320
Wait, so you've been
watching me this whole time?

737
00:40:32,453 --> 00:40:33,854
Even in the shower?

738
00:40:33,988 --> 00:40:35,890
That's a trick question.

739
00:40:36,023 --> 00:40:38,292
Sonic the Hedgehog
prefers bubble baths.

740
00:40:38,426 --> 00:40:39,627
Man, you're good!

741
00:40:39,759 --> 00:40:42,063
When I learned Knuckles
was on your trail,

742
