00:53:49,384 --> 00:53:52,854
And what kind of genius
shows up to Siberia
in a convertible?

985
00:53:52,987 --> 00:53:56,224
The kind of genius
that can turn up the heat...

986
00:53:57,992 --> 00:53:59,961
with a flick of a switch.

987
00:54:05,933 --> 00:54:07,001
[grunts]

988
00:54:07,634 --> 00:54:10,471
Oh! Whoo! [laughs]

989
00:54:11,339 --> 00:54:14,142
Good one!
I'm sure that wasn't important.

990
00:54:16,477 --> 00:54:18,880
Tails, that's our exit.
Come on.

991
00:54:24,085 --> 00:54:25,286
[growls]

992
00:54:28,423 --> 00:54:29,790
[yelps]

993
00:54:31,725 --> 00:54:33,660
Uh-huh.
Let's split up.

994
00:54:33,794 --> 00:54:35,363
You go high, I go low.

995
00:54:35,496 --> 00:54:36,563
Right.

996
00:54:36,696 --> 00:54:39,067
Quick little stretch
and here we go.

997
00:54:40,268 --> 00:54:42,270
[laughs]

998
00:54:50,511 --> 00:54:52,113
[Sonic]
Oh, so you want to play?

999
00:54:57,151 --> 00:54:58,652
That's new.

1000
00:54:58,785 --> 00:55:01,022
Whoa. [screams]

1001
00:55:07,095 --> 00:55:08,695
[exclaiming]

1002
00:55:10,064 --> 00:55:11,332
Sonic!

1003
00:55:11,466 --> 00:55:12,467
[yells]

1004
00:55:12,599 --> 00:55:14,634
[yelping]

1005
00:55:24,412 --> 00:55:26,013
Snowball fight!

1006
00:55:29,649 --> 00:55:31,052
[Sonic laughs]

1007
00:55:31,185 --> 00:55:35,423
It's too easy.
Come on, challenge me!

1008
00:55:35,556 --> 00:55:37,024
[gasps]

1009
00:55:40,694 --> 00:55:42,662
["A Summer Place" playing]

1010
00:55:44,265 --> 00:55:49,036
♪ <i>There's a summer place</i> ♪

1011
00:55:49,170 --> 00:55:52,073
[Sonic] We are talking style
and pizzazz.

1012
00:55:52,206 --> 00:55:54,976
♪ <i>Where it may rain or storm</i> ♪

1013
00:55:55,109 --> 00:55:56,978
Pew-pew-pew!
Pew, pew, pew, pew, pew, pew.

1014
00:55:57,111 --> 00:55:58,846
♪ <i>Yet I'm safe and warm</i> ♪

1015
00:55:58,980 --> 00:56:02,350
Yeah!
I make this look good.

1016
00:56:03,417 --> 00:56:04,552
[grunts]

1017
00:56:04,684 --> 00:56:07,054
Oh, great.
The Winter Soldier.

1018
00:56:13,561 --> 00:56:16,397
For a guy named Knuckles,
you are really bad at punching.

1019
00:56:16,531 --> 00:56:19,901
Surrender the compass!
You are no match for me.

1020
00:56:20,034 --> 00:56:22,436
I've been training for this
my entire life.

1021
00:56:22,570 --> 00:56:26,040
And I had no training at all,
yet here I am ahead of you.

1022
00:56:26,174 --> 00:56:28,675
That's gotta be
embarrassing.

1023
00:56:29,844 --> 00:56:31,179
[yelps]

1024
00:56:33,680 --> 00:56:35,983
[gasps] My rings!

1025
00:56:39,020 --> 00:56:42,823
Has anyone ever told you
you've got serious anger issues?

1026
00:56:42,957 --> 00:56:44,992
You mock me
with your weak jokes,

1027
00:56:45,126 --> 00:56:47,028
but you know nothing
about me, hedgehog.

1028
00:56:47,161 --> 00:56:51,499
Well, I know you Echidnas
have a habit of showing up
uninvited and ruining my life.

1029
00:56:51,632 --> 00:56:54,902
Ruining your life?
Another bad joke.

1030
00:56:55,036 --> 00:56:57,638
I lost everything
because of you.

1031
00:56:57,771 --> 00:57:01,142
<i>My tribe was on the verge</i>
<i>of its greatest victory.</i>

1032
00:57:01,275 --> 00:57:04,111
<i>The last of the Owl warriors</i>
<i>had been located.</i>

1033
00:57:04,245 --> 00:57:07,982
<i>Soon Longclaw's Emerald secrets</i>
<i>would be ours.</i>

1034
00:57:08,115 --> 00:57:11,219
<i>But my father stopped me</i>
<i>from joining the fight.</i>

1035
00:57:11,352 --> 00:57:14,922
<i>He said my moment</i>
<i>to honor our tribe would come,</i>

1036
00:57:15,056 --> 00:57:17,091
<i>but it was not this moment.</i>

1037
00:57:17,225 --> 00:57:19,860
<i>Those were the last words</i>
<i>he spoke to me.</i>

1038
00:57:19,994 --> 00:57:22,496
I never saw him again.

1039
00:57:23,931 --> 00:57:26,766
We both lost everything
that day.

1040
00:57:27,734 --> 00:57:28,735
[Echidnas yelling]

1041
00:57:28,869 --> 00:57:30,438
Goodbye, Sonic.
No!

1042
00:57:30,571 --> 00:57:32,506
<i>Longclaw!</i>

1043
00:57:34,442 --> 00:57:36,043
[groaning]

1044
00:57:36,711 --> 00:57:38,546
Sonic! Are you okay?

1045
00:57:38,679 --> 00:57:40,381
Deceiver!

1046
00:57:40,514 --> 00:57:42,917
No,
it wasn't a trick.

1047
00:57:43,050 --> 00:57:46,120
Tails, take the compass
and get out of here!

1048
00:57:49,257 --> 00:57:50,291
Yeah!

1049
00:57:51,559 --> 00:57:53,527
Later, haters!

1050
00:57:56,763 --> 00:57:58,099
Tails!

1051
00:58:05,006 --> 00:58:06,407
Tails, come on.
Wake up.

1052
00:58:06,540 --> 00:58:09,410
He chose helping the fox
over pursuing the compass.

1053
00:58:09,543 --> 00:58:10,878
Of course he did.

1054
00:58:11,012 --> 00:58:13,614
New friend,
same pathetic weakness.

1055
00:58:13,748 --> 00:58:16,150
Hmm.

1056
00:58:16,284 --> 00:58:18,119
[rumbling]

1057
00:58:18,252 --> 00:58:19,387
[gasps]

1058
00:58:23,724 --> 00:58:26,394
Oh, no. No, no, no.
We're in real trouble here.

1059
00:58:26,527 --> 00:58:29,964
Come on, Tails. I need you
to fly us out of here.
Time to wake up.

1060
00:58:37,271 --> 00:58:40,808
See ya, kids.
Enjoy the fresh powder.

1061
00:58:42,443 --> 00:58:44,378
[grunting]

1062
00:58:44,512 --> 00:58:47,915
[ukulele music playing]

1063
00:58:50,017 --> 00:58:51,452
[guests murmuring]

1064
00:58:54,822 --> 00:58:58,059
[airplane passing overhead]

1065
00:58:58,793 --> 00:59:01,462
[guests applauding]

1066
00:59:06,000 --> 00:59:07,301
Did you...

1067
00:59:12,673 --> 00:59:15,343
These rings signify the--

1068
00:59:15,476 --> 00:59:17,845
[phone ringtone]

1069
00:59:21,082 --> 00:59:22,750
[laughs] Sorry.

1070
00:59:22,883 --> 00:59:24,552
Thought it was on silent.
[ringtone stops]

1071
00:59:31,025 --> 00:59:33,461
These rings--
[phone ringtone]

1072
00:59:34,528 --> 00:59:35,996
So help me, Thomas!

1073
00:59:37,031 --> 00:59:39,367
[stammering]

1074
00:59:40,634 --> 00:59:41,936
Okay, sorry. Sorry.

1075
00:59:42,069 --> 00:59:43,938
Excuse me,
this is an emergency.

1076
00:59:45,506 --> 00:59:47,174
Sorry.

1077
00:59:49,944 --> 00:59:51,545
[phone ringing]

1078
00:59:51,679 --> 00:59:54,615
What?
This better be important.
I just--

1079
00:59:54,749 --> 00:59:56,183
<i>Are you skiing?</i>

1080
00:59:56,317 --> 00:59:58,252
<i>Snowboarding, actually.</i>
<i>But I need your help now.</i>

1081
00:59:58,386 --> 01:00:00,588
Life or death situation
this very second.

1082
01:00:00,721 --> 01:00:03,591
I need you to use the ring
I gave you to save me.
Like right now.

1083
01:00:03,724 --> 01:00:06,060
<i>Okay, slow down.</i>
<i>I don't even know</i>
<i>where you are.</i>

1084
01:00:06,193 --> 01:00:08,496
You just gotta picture
where you want the ring to go.

1085
01:00:08,629 --> 01:00:09,964
So picture this.

1086
01:00:12,366 --> 01:00:15,236
Oh, my God.
Okay, okay. Hang on.

1087
01:00:22,977 --> 01:00:24,612
What?

1088
01:00:26,113 --> 01:00:28,082
[Sonic] <i>Did you throw it?</i>

1089
01:00:28,215 --> 01:00:30,518
Oh, God.
[Sonic] <i>What?</i>
<i>Tell me what "Oh, God."</i>

1090
01:00:30,651 --> 01:00:32,219
I mixed up the rings
when I was teasing Jojo.

1091
01:00:32,353 --> 01:00:34,121
<i>What?</i>
<i>Where is it then?</i>

1092
01:00:38,325 --> 01:00:39,493
You don't want to know.

1093
01:00:39,627 --> 01:00:40,829
<i>But I do, Tom.</i>

1094
01:00:40,961 --> 01:00:42,196
[sighs]
<i>I very much want to know,</i>

1095
01:00:42,329 --> 01:00:44,799
before I become
a hedgehog-flavored snow cone.

1096
01:00:44,932 --> 01:00:46,934
Hang tight, buddy.
I got this.

1097
01:00:47,067 --> 01:00:48,837
With this ring, Rachel...

1098
01:00:48,969 --> 01:00:50,704
Hey! Hi.
[guests gasp]

1099
01:00:50,839 --> 01:00:52,706
Uh...
Everything okay, bud?

1100
01:00:52,841 --> 01:00:54,508
Not really.
What are you doing?

1101
01:00:54,642 --> 01:00:56,944
This is gonna sound crazy,
but I need to see that ring

1102
01:00:57,077 --> 01:00:59,280
for just one second.
Have you lost your mind?

1103
01:00:59,413 --> 01:01:01,048
I'm gonna give it
right back, I promise.

1104
01:01:01,182 --> 01:01:03,852
Please, Randall,
it's really important.
No, bro. Go sit down.

1105
01:01:03,984 --> 01:01:07,087
Give me the ring, please?
Randall, don't look at him,
look at me.

1106
01:01:07,221 --> 01:01:08,824
One second.
Put the ring on my finger.

1107
01:01:08,956 --> 01:01:10,324
No, Randall,
listen to me.

1108
01:01:10,458 --> 01:01:12,159
Randall! Look at me.
Ring on my finger.

1109
01:01:12,293 --> 01:01:15,062
Give me the ring!
Just one second.
Put a ring on it!

1110
01:01:15,663 --> 01:01:16,898
Please, love? Okay?

1111
01:01:17,031 --> 01:01:17,965
With this ring--
Yes, baby.

1112
01:01:18,098 --> 01:01:19,835
I'm so sorry
about this.

1113
01:01:19,967 --> 01:01:21,669
[grunts]
[guests exclaiming]

1114
01:01:23,839 --> 01:01:25,473
[grunts]

1115
01:01:26,507 --> 01:01:28,108
[gasps]

1116
01:01:30,044 --> 01:01:32,379
Snow, my God.
Oh, boy.

1117
01:01:32,980 --> 01:01:34,448
Incoming!

1118
01:01:34,582 --> 01:01:35,616
[guests screaming]

1119
01:01:38,954 --> 01:01:40,521
[Sonic] Oh.

1120
01:01:41,989 --> 01:01:45,192
[guests groaning,
chattering]

1121
01:01:45,961 --> 01:01:47,428
Anybody hurt?

1122
01:01:47,561 --> 01:01:49,530
Sonic!
Hawaii.

1123
01:01:49,663 --> 01:01:50,764
Are you okay?

1124
01:01:50,899 --> 01:01:52,766
What's happening?
Are you hurt?
[groaning]

1125
01:01:52,901 --> 01:01:54,602
No, no, I'm fine.
Okay, good.

1126
01:01:54,735 --> 01:01:56,237
Because you're in
so much trouble!

1127
01:01:56,370 --> 01:01:58,506
Okay, you calm down.

1128
01:01:58,639 --> 01:01:59,841
You talk.

1129
01:01:59,975 --> 01:02:01,475
Okay, quick version.

1130
01:02:01,609 --> 01:02:03,879
Robotnik is back on Earth
and he's after a magic emerald.

1131
01:02:04,011 --> 01:02:05,246
[grunts, sighs]

1132
01:02:05,379 --> 01:02:08,516
We need to get it back
or the world is doomed.

1133
01:02:09,049 --> 01:02:10,184
Tails!

1134
01:02:10,317 --> 01:02:12,319
Wait! All this happened
since yesterday?

1135
01:02:12,453 --> 01:02:13,721
Wait.
Who's Tails?

1136
01:02:13,855 --> 01:02:14,990
Tails, can you hear me?

1137
01:02:15,122 --> 01:02:17,024
Oh, Lord,
there are two of them now.

1138
01:02:17,157 --> 01:02:19,426
Okay, let me think.
Tails, come on, buddy.

1139
01:02:19,560 --> 01:02:22,029
[Sonic groaning]

1140
01:02:22,663 --> 01:02:23,965
[weapons powering up]

1141
01:02:24,098 --> 01:02:25,432
Hey!

1142
01:02:25,566 --> 01:02:28,035
Randall,
why do all of your friends
have weapons?

1143
01:02:29,670 --> 01:02:33,307
You really should have
taken me up on that brunch,
Mr. and Mrs. Wachowski.

1144
01:02:33,808 --> 01:02:35,142
Olive Garden guy?

1145
01:02:35,276 --> 01:02:38,045
It's okay, everyone.
We're federal agents.

1146
01:02:38,178 --> 01:02:41,081
You, too, Agent.
Go ahead.

1147
01:02:47,254 --> 01:02:48,756
You mean to tell me

1148
01:02:48,890 --> 01:02:52,027
that this entire wedding
was a setup?
Rachel, wait a minute.

1149
01:02:52,159 --> 01:02:53,093
What?

1150
01:02:53,227 --> 01:02:54,361
That's correct, ma'am.

1151
01:02:54,495 --> 01:02:56,130
Every single aspect
of Operation Catfish

1152
01:02:56,263 --> 01:02:58,098
was a complete fabrication.

1153
01:02:59,000 --> 01:03:00,267
Operation Catfish?

1154
01:03:00,401 --> 01:03:03,137
So is everyone here
an agent?

1155
01:03:04,204 --> 01:03:05,573
Are you an agent?

1156
01:03:06,206 --> 01:03:07,608
Son of a...

1157
01:03:07,741 --> 01:03:11,145
Was the florist an agent?
How about the photographer?

1158
01:03:11,278 --> 01:03:13,547
The woman who waxed my...

1159
01:03:14,315 --> 01:03:15,616
at the spa?

1160
01:03:17,084 --> 01:03:18,053
Is Jojo an agent?

1161
01:03:18,185 --> 01:03:19,520
[Randall] Rachel.

1162
01:03:19,653 --> 01:03:20,956
What?

1163
01:03:21,088 --> 01:03:22,057
Rachel, listen to me.

1164
01:03:22,189 --> 01:03:23,324
I'm done listening!

1165
01:03:23,457 --> 01:03:25,559
I am done listening!

1166
01:03:25,693 --> 01:03:28,830
I am so sorry.
I am so sorry.
[sobbing]

1167
01:03:28,964 --> 01:03:30,664
I really am.
I am so sorry.

1168
01:03:32,600 --> 01:03:34,568
No. Hey, no!

1169
01:03:34,702 --> 01:03:37,338
Let him go! Hey!

1170
01:03:39,808 --> 01:03:40,741
[grunts]

1171
01:03:40,875 --> 01:03:42,376
Sonic, hang on.

1172
01:03:42,509 --> 01:03:43,979
Take it easy.
It's not worth it.

1173
01:03:44,111 --> 01:03:45,613
Tom!
Ah-ah-ah.

1174
01:03:45,746 --> 01:03:48,349
Sonic is not a threat.
He's on our side.

1175
01:03:48,482 --> 01:03:50,351
He's an uncontrolled
extraterrestrial.

1176
01:03:50,484 --> 01:03:52,486
And your days of aiding
and abetting him are over.

1177
01:03:52,620 --> 01:03:55,322
Secure them in the hotel
until the chopper arrives.

1178
01:03:55,456 --> 01:03:57,324
You're making a mistake.

1179
01:03:57,458 --> 01:03:59,660
[Rachel]
Hold on, Major A-hole!

1180
01:03:59,793 --> 01:04:01,228
This is still my day,

1181
01:04:01,362 --> 01:04:05,066
and someone
is gonna explain to me
what the hell is going on here!

1182
01:04:05,199 --> 01:04:06,500
After the events
in San Francisco,

1183
01:04:06,634 --> 01:04:08,402
a global task force
was created,

1184
01:04:08,535 --> 01:04:11,639
devoted to protecting
our planet from alien threats.

1185
01:04:11,772 --> 01:04:14,441
That day,
Guardian Units of Nations
was born.

1186
01:04:14,575 --> 01:04:16,978
G-U-N.
Seriously?
GUN, yeah.

1187
01:04:17,112 --> 01:04:20,214
Look, what about protecting
our planet from Dr. Robotnik?

1188
01:04:21,248 --> 01:04:22,483
Robotnik is dead.

1189
01:04:22,616 --> 01:04:24,618
You're wrong.
He's back.

1190
01:04:24,752 --> 01:04:27,521
And you just hauled away
the only ones
who could stop him.

1191
01:04:29,924 --> 01:04:32,027
Sounds like Robotnik
might be back in play.

1192
01:04:32,159 --> 01:04:34,795
If he is,
I want him found immediately.

1193
01:04:35,830 --> 01:04:38,432
And cancel my five o'clock
at the Olive Garden.

1194
01:04:38,565 --> 01:04:40,200
Aunt Maddie?
Yeah.

1195
01:04:40,334 --> 01:04:42,302
Sonic and his friend
dropped this.

1196
01:04:44,271 --> 01:04:46,674
[gadgets beeping]

1197
01:04:48,943 --> 01:04:50,210
I have an idea.

1198
01:04:50,344 --> 01:04:52,413
And I want to have
a word with my fiancé.

1199
01:04:52,546 --> 01:04:54,481
And that word
is "murder."

1200
01:04:58,786 --> 01:05:01,588
[Sonic] Hey, come on.
You can't just leave us in here.

1201
01:05:01,722 --> 01:05:05,259
My friend is hurt!
He needs a doctor,
a vet, anyone!

1202
01:05:06,293 --> 01:05:07,795
Tails,
you got to wake up, buddy.

1203
01:05:07,929 --> 01:05:09,563
Please wake up.

1204
01:05:09,697 --> 01:05:12,533
[children chattering, laughing]

1205
01:05:15,402 --> 01:05:16,805
[police radio chatter]

1206
01:05:16,938 --> 01:05:18,807
All clear.

1207
01:05:22,276 --> 01:05:23,978
All right.
Game plan.

1208
01:05:24,112 --> 01:05:26,714
I get inside the hotel
and find where they're hiding
Tom and Sonic.

1209
01:05:26,848 --> 01:05:28,482
Okay.
Then I find Randall, right?

1210
01:05:28,615 --> 01:05:29,951
And then I squeeze
the breath

1211
01:05:30,085 --> 01:05:34,221
from his lying, deceitful,
perfectly manscaped body!

1212
01:05:34,354 --> 01:05:36,457
[cackles]

1213
01:05:36,590 --> 01:05:38,325
I'm going through
a lot right now.

1214
01:05:38,459 --> 01:05:40,128
So let me process this
my own way, okay?

1215
01:05:40,260 --> 01:05:41,528
Sure, sure.

1216
01:05:41,662 --> 01:05:43,865
No judgment.
Should've brought
a journal.

1217
01:05:43,998 --> 01:05:45,432
Okay--

1218
01:05:45,566 --> 01:05:48,937
Okay. Is this meant
to be a weapon?
This is adorable.

1219
01:05:49,070 --> 01:05:51,106
Pew, pew!
Take that, Randall!

1220
01:05:51,238 --> 01:05:53,208
[imitates explosion]
Run, Randall!

1221
01:05:53,340 --> 01:05:54,608
All right.

1222
01:05:54,742 --> 01:05:56,610
We're about
to find out.
All right!

1223
01:05:56,744 --> 01:05:59,346
Let's go kick some booty.
[laughs]

1224
01:06:01,281 --> 01:06:02,951
[Maddie] Shh! Shh!

1225
01:06:12,193 --> 01:06:13,794
Rachel! No. Rachel!

1226
01:06:14,996 --> 01:06:16,296
In a minute.

1227
01:06:17,165 --> 01:06:18,732
Mm-mmm! Mm.

1228
01:06:21,836 --> 01:06:23,238
Stop right there!

1229
01:06:23,370 --> 01:06:24,772
Get the bag.

1230
01:06:27,242 --> 01:06:28,542
[device beeping]

1231
01:06:29,878 --> 01:06:31,512
[screaming]

1232
01:06:32,713 --> 01:06:34,281
He's gonna
come back down, right?

1233
01:06:34,414 --> 01:06:35,917
I don't know.
[groans]

1234
01:06:36,050 --> 01:06:37,284
Good luck!

1235
01:06:38,987 --> 01:06:41,388
Look. Tom and Sonic
have to be inside.

1236
01:06:41,522 --> 01:06:43,992
I got a fiancé
to vaporize.
Uh-huh.

1237
01:06:44,125 --> 01:06:45,492
Watch your back,
sis.
Okay.

1238
01:06:45,626 --> 01:06:48,295
[both grunting, growls]

1239
01:06:48,428 --> 01:06:49,663
Randall!

1240
01:06:53,767 --> 01:06:54,869
[grunts]

1241
01:06:56,503 --> 01:06:57,671
We got her.

1242
01:06:57,806 --> 01:06:59,406
Move in.

1243
01:07:03,011 --> 01:07:04,045
Okay.

1244
01:07:09,250 --> 01:07:10,617
[grunts]

1245
01:07:10,751 --> 01:07:11,953
[grunts]

1246
01:07:12,086 --> 01:07:13,420
[grunts]

1247
01:07:20,261 --> 01:07:22,429
I did not mean to do that!

1248
01:07:24,331 --> 01:07:26,400
Whoo!

1249
01:07:34,775 --> 01:07:36,710
Something bothering you,
Agent?

1250
01:07:36,845 --> 01:07:39,314
I just feel a little guilty
about what I did to Rachel, sir.

1251
01:07:39,446 --> 01:07:43,017
Ah, don't worry about it.
We'll send her a gift card.

1252
01:07:43,151 --> 01:07:45,485
Now,
I propose a toast.

1253
01:07:48,422 --> 01:07:51,192
To a perfectly
executed operation.

1254
01:07:51,326 --> 01:07:52,927
[agent screaming]

1255
01:07:55,796 --> 01:07:57,464
Sir, we're under attack.

1256
01:07:57,598 --> 01:07:59,067
["Barracuda" playing]

1257
01:07:59,200 --> 01:08:01,568
[crashing]
[glass shattering]

1258
01:08:06,406 --> 01:08:08,810
[crashing continues]

1259
01:08:17,819 --> 01:08:22,456
Randall, wifey's home!
[cackles]

1260
01:08:26,194 --> 01:08:27,929
Oh, my God. Rachel.

1261
01:08:29,763 --> 01:08:32,100
♪ <i>You lying so low</i>
<i>In the weeds</i> ♪

1262
01:08:32,233 --> 01:08:33,567
[tires screeching]

1263
01:08:33,700 --> 01:08:36,204
♪ <i>I bet you gonna ambush me</i> ♪

1264
01:08:36,337 --> 01:08:41,910
♪ <i>You'd have me down, down</i>
<i>Down, down on my knees</i> ♪

1265
01:08:42,043 --> 01:08:44,711
♪ <i>Now wouldn't you, barracuda?</i> ♪

1266
01:08:47,148 --> 01:08:48,983
♪ <i>Oh</i> ♪

1267
01:08:52,452 --> 01:08:55,555
What a woman.

1268
01:08:57,457 --> 01:08:58,860
You no-good,

1269
01:08:59,827 --> 01:09:02,763
lowdown, dirty, lying--

1270
01:09:02,897 --> 01:09:04,198
Rachel,
just listen to me.

1271
01:09:04,332 --> 01:09:05,766
What kind of twisted sicko

1272
01:09:05,900 --> 01:09:08,468
tricks someone
into a fake wedding?

1273
01:09:08,602 --> 01:09:10,104
[weapon clicks, powers up]

1274
01:09:10,238 --> 01:09:13,808
Party's over, Bridezilla.
Stop right there.

1275
01:09:14,508 --> 01:09:16,543
You son of a--

1276
01:09:16,677 --> 01:09:18,745
Have it your way.
No!

1277
01:09:18,880 --> 01:09:20,815
No!
[electrodes buzzing]

1278
01:09:21,316 --> 01:09:23,151
[groaning]

1279
01:09:23,284 --> 01:09:25,386
Oh. Ugh. Oh!

1280
01:09:25,519 --> 01:09:28,022
Very disappointing,
Agent Handel.

1281
01:09:30,058 --> 01:09:32,093
Ha! Is that supposed
to be a weapon?

1282
01:09:32,226 --> 01:09:33,995
I don't know,
but we gonna find out.

1283
01:09:34,128 --> 01:09:36,596
Haven't you caused
enough trouble for one day?

1284
01:09:36,730 --> 01:09:39,566
I haven't even begun
causing trouble.

1285
01:09:39,700 --> 01:09:43,037
Hell hath no fury like
a bride scorned.

1286
01:09:49,676 --> 01:09:53,480
Looks like it's real, huh?
[laughs]

1287
01:09:54,349 --> 01:09:56,184
Whoa! Uh! Ah! Huh?

1288
01:09:56,317 --> 01:09:57,819
No. Right.

1289
01:09:59,519 --> 01:10:01,923
Be honest. How bad is it?

1290
01:10:02,056 --> 01:10:05,592
Not bad at all.
You got Tased. You'll be fine.

1291
01:10:09,464 --> 01:10:10,465
I'm so cold.

1292
01:10:10,597 --> 01:10:13,301
You landed on
our ice sculpture.

1293
01:10:13,434 --> 01:10:14,735
Get up.

1294
01:10:20,574 --> 01:10:21,943
Just--

1295
01:10:22,076 --> 01:10:24,912
Just tell me the truth,
for once.

1296
01:10:25,046 --> 01:10:30,684
Is there anything about you
or about us that was real?

1297
01:10:31,285 --> 01:10:34,489
Rachel, look at me.

1298
01:10:34,621 --> 01:10:36,556
Before I met you,

1299
01:10:36,690 --> 01:10:39,760
I didn't think
that I was even capable
of real happiness.

1300
01:10:41,062 --> 01:10:43,530
But that all changed
when you walked
into my life.

1301
01:10:43,663 --> 01:10:47,301
And I ended up breaking
the first rule
of undercover work.

1302
01:10:47,435 --> 01:10:49,370
Which is?

1303
01:10:49,504 --> 01:10:51,772
Never fall in love.

1304
01:11:02,450 --> 01:11:04,018
[door lock beeps, clicks]

1305
01:11:04,152 --> 01:11:05,987
[Tom] Maddie!
[Sonic] Maddie!

1306
01:11:06,120 --> 01:11:08,588
We're busting out of here.
How'd you get past
the guards?

1307
01:11:08,722 --> 01:11:10,525
Because that little fox
is into some crazy stuff.

1308
01:11:10,657 --> 01:11:13,061
Come on.
[laughing]

1309
01:11:13,194 --> 01:11:15,129
Let's go.
You're amazing.

1310
01:11:25,440 --> 01:11:28,608
The Owls were fools to think
they could hide this.

1311
01:11:36,616 --> 01:11:38,186
Ah.

1312
01:11:41,422 --> 01:11:43,257
[chiming]

1313
01:11:43,391 --> 01:11:45,359
[rumbling]

1314
01:12:06,280 --> 01:12:08,116
What's happening?

1315
01:12:09,584 --> 01:12:11,352
Wait for it.

1316
01:12:16,491 --> 01:12:18,459
[exclaims]

1317
01:12:18,593 --> 01:12:22,629
[cackling]

1318
01:12:22,762 --> 01:12:25,199
Yes. Eureka!

1319
01:12:26,334 --> 01:12:28,136
I've found it!

1320
01:12:36,577 --> 01:12:38,146
[explosion]

1321
01:12:47,488 --> 01:12:48,823
Sonic.

1322
01:12:50,558 --> 01:12:53,094
What is that?
A big problem.

1323
01:12:53,227 --> 01:12:55,062
The compass led Robotnik
to the Emerald.

1324
01:12:55,196 --> 01:12:57,431
That's got to be
hundreds of miles away.

1325
01:12:58,765 --> 01:13:00,067
All right.

1326
01:13:00,201 --> 01:13:02,236
Huddle up.
Let's figure out a plan.

1327
01:13:02,370 --> 01:13:03,337
Together.

1328
01:13:03,471 --> 01:13:04,805
There's no time for that.

1329
01:13:04,939 --> 01:13:06,474
I'm the only one
that can get there fast enough.

1330
01:13:06,607 --> 01:13:09,143
Sonic, this is way too big
for you to do by yourself.

1331
01:13:09,277 --> 01:13:11,212
You see that little fox
over there?

1332
01:13:11,345 --> 01:13:14,882
He came all the way
across the universe
to meet his hero.

1333
01:13:15,016 --> 01:13:18,186
And what did his hero do?
I practically got him killed.

1334
01:13:18,853 --> 01:13:21,122
You know what?
You were right.

1335
01:13:21,255 --> 01:13:23,558
My moment came
and I blew it.

1336
01:13:23,690 --> 01:13:24,859
I'm no hero.

1337
01:13:24,992 --> 01:13:26,160
Wait.
[Sonic] No.

1338
01:13:26,294 --> 01:13:27,662
I'm not letting
anyone else get hurt

1339
01:13:27,794 --> 01:13:28,930
because of me.

1340
01:13:29,063 --> 01:13:30,865
I'm gonna fix this
while I still can.

1341
01:13:32,033 --> 01:13:33,668
Sonic!
[gasps]

1342
01:13:33,801 --> 01:13:36,204
Sonic, wait!
[grunts]

1343
01:13:36,337 --> 01:13:37,872
[groaning]

1344
01:13:38,005 --> 01:13:40,774
Hold on. Wait.
Don't move.

1345
01:13:40,908 --> 01:13:42,577
Take it easy, little guy.
You're hurt.

1346
01:13:42,709 --> 01:13:46,414
But we have to help him.
You don't know
what he's up against.

1347
01:13:53,554 --> 01:13:55,089
You believe us now?

1348
01:13:56,857 --> 01:13:58,492
Mm-hmm.

1349
01:13:58,626 --> 01:14:00,061
[siren wailing]

1350
01:14:00,194 --> 01:14:02,029
["You Know How We Do It"
playing]

1351
01:14:02,163 --> 01:14:02,997
Hey, Bob!

1352
01:14:03,130 --> 01:14:05,032
Hey, Maria,
how you doing?
Hey!

1353
01:14:05,166 --> 01:14:06,300
Ah.

1354
01:14:08,402 --> 01:14:09,537
Working on my moves.

1355
01:14:09,670 --> 01:14:12,073
Just keepin' it green.
No need to burn the fuel.

1356
01:14:12,206 --> 01:14:14,375
Speaking of fuel--
[groans]

1357
01:14:19,746 --> 01:14:22,483
Closed? [sighs]

1358
01:14:22,617 --> 01:14:24,118
That doesn't seem right.

1359
01:14:28,990 --> 01:14:31,993
[electronic beeping]

1360
01:14:36,731 --> 01:14:37,999
Close.

1361
01:14:42,403 --> 01:14:43,571
Yes.

1362
01:14:43,704 --> 01:14:46,274
Makeover, makeover.
Look at you.

1363
01:14:46,407 --> 01:14:47,908
Freeze! Police!

1364
01:14:48,976 --> 01:14:50,978
Oh, my God,
you got robot hands.

1365
01:14:51,112 --> 01:14:52,246
No, they're gloves.

1366
01:14:52,380 --> 01:14:54,849
Get 'em up.
Now spread your fingers!

1367
01:14:55,916 --> 01:14:58,785
Now wiggle 'em!
Wiggle your digits!

1368
01:14:59,954 --> 01:15:02,923
Yes! Like you just finished
a big musical number.

1369
01:15:04,558 --> 01:15:05,960
Good.

1370
01:15:06,093 --> 01:15:07,828
Why is there
a light on your head?

1371
01:15:11,332 --> 01:15:13,801
'Cause I'm the sheriff
for the weekend, pal.

1372
01:15:21,809 --> 01:15:23,577
[Sonic] Ugh. Water.

1373
01:15:23,711 --> 01:15:25,846
Why did it have to be water?

1374
01:15:27,415 --> 01:15:28,416
[exhales]

1375
01:15:28,549 --> 01:15:31,452
Okay, you can do this.

1376
01:15:34,922 --> 01:15:36,824
Gotta go fast.

1377
01:15:56,610 --> 01:15:59,580
[grunting]

1378
01:16:00,648 --> 01:16:02,249
[Sonic yells]

1379
01:16:03,017 --> 01:16:05,519
[yelling]

1380
01:16:12,026 --> 01:16:14,662
[panting]

1381
01:16:14,795 --> 01:16:17,932
[straining]

1382
01:16:33,347 --> 01:16:35,049
[coughing]

1383
01:16:45,493 --> 01:16:47,661
[gasps]

1384
01:17:06,414 --> 01:17:07,915
Oh!

1385
01:17:10,852 --> 01:17:12,286
[grunts]

1386
01:17:18,894 --> 01:17:22,596
I don't want
to die like this!
It's derivative!

1387
01:17:23,998 --> 01:17:25,966
Make room for Daddy!

1388
01:17:27,568 --> 01:17:29,036
[grunting]

1389
01:17:33,707 --> 01:17:35,476
Two and two.
Great!

1390
01:17:35,609 --> 01:17:38,679
We're still bipedals,
more or less.
[sighs]

1391
01:17:41,549 --> 01:17:43,217
Fire in the hole!

1392
01:17:44,952 --> 01:17:48,556
I've solved it.
There is a booby trap
every seven seco--

1393
01:17:55,062 --> 01:17:57,031
That was a little early.
Mmm.

1394
01:17:57,164 --> 01:18:01,368
Oh! So glad it didn't
cut off my mustache.

1395
01:18:01,502 --> 01:18:04,572
Hey,
Little Red Wrecking Ball.

1396
01:18:04,705 --> 01:18:06,908
I know you're dying
to get your Emerald on,

1397
01:18:07,041 --> 01:18:11,479
but can we be
a little bit more mindful
of our surroundings?

1398
01:18:11,612 --> 01:18:12,580
May I?

1399
01:18:12,713 --> 01:18:14,181
[glove beeping]

1400
01:18:19,153 --> 01:18:21,755
[electronic voice]
<i>In 30 feet, turn left.</i>

1401
01:18:21,890 --> 01:18:24,024
Work smarter, not harder.

1402
01:18:38,305 --> 01:18:41,509
[Sonic yelling]

1403
01:18:42,610 --> 01:18:45,012
[grunting, groans]

1404
01:18:45,145 --> 01:18:46,680
My pelvis.

1405
01:18:50,751 --> 01:18:55,289
Okay, Secret Temple,
let's see what you've got.

1406
01:19:01,462 --> 01:19:03,163
Whoa!

1407
01:19:03,297 --> 01:19:05,132
No, no, no! No!

1408
01:19:05,599 --> 01:19:07,067
[yells]

1409
01:19:07,201 --> 01:19:09,537
[exclaiming]

1410
01:19:09,670 --> 01:19:10,704
No.

1411
01:19:11,806 --> 01:19:13,774
Yes! [screams]

1412
01:19:18,579 --> 01:19:20,447
[electronic voice]
<i>You have arrived</i>
<i>at your destination.</i>

1413
01:19:20,581 --> 01:19:23,584
Wow. That really
opened up the space.

1414
01:19:23,717 --> 01:19:26,554
I can't even picture it
with an impenetrable wall now.

1415
01:19:26,687 --> 01:19:29,056
And the rubble
is always a nice touch.

1416
01:19:37,999 --> 01:19:41,702
At last.
The Master Emerald.

1417
01:19:41,836 --> 01:19:42,971
Ultimate power.

1418
01:19:43,103 --> 01:19:45,706
Soon order
will be restored.

1419
01:19:45,840 --> 01:19:49,243
All because of what
we have done together.

1420
01:19:49,376 --> 01:19:52,079
Such a lovely sentiment,
Knuckles.

1421
01:19:52,212 --> 01:19:55,115
I think I feel
a single tear forming.

1422
01:19:57,852 --> 01:19:58,987
Sadly...

1423
01:19:59,119 --> 01:20:00,154
[crackling]

1424
01:20:00,287 --> 01:20:01,355
...you're as useful
to me now

1425
01:20:01,488 --> 01:20:05,326
as a backstage pass
to Limp Bizkit.

1426
01:20:05,459 --> 01:20:07,862
[thudding]
[Sonic yelling]
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

1427
01:20:07,996 --> 01:20:09,430
[Sonic yelling]

1428
01:20:11,165 --> 01:20:13,233
[yelling continues]

1429
01:20:13,367 --> 01:20:15,269
[metal clanking]
[Sonic grunting]

1430
01:20:15,402 --> 01:20:17,605
[yells, grunts]

1431
01:20:17,738 --> 01:20:19,406
[coughing]

1432
01:20:19,540 --> 01:20:20,474
Nailed it.

1433
01:20:20,608 --> 01:20:21,675
[gasps]

1434
01:20:21,810 --> 01:20:25,880
This guy is always trying
to spoil a bad thing!

1435
01:20:26,014 --> 01:20:27,648
Ah! You guys
are here, too?

1436
01:20:27,781 --> 01:20:29,017
Took the long way, huh?

1437
01:20:29,149 --> 01:20:31,218
Is everything a joke
to you?

1438
01:20:31,352 --> 01:20:34,055
Why must you
constantly interfere
with my destiny?

1439
01:20:34,188 --> 01:20:38,059
Because my destiny
is to protect my friends
and family.

1440
01:20:38,192 --> 01:20:40,061
I think I just threw up
in my mouth.

1441
01:20:40,227 --> 01:20:46,567
And if you want that emerald,
you're gonna have
to go through me.

1442
01:20:47,201 --> 01:20:48,502
[gulps]

1443
01:20:51,973 --> 01:20:53,440
Whoa!

1444
01:20:57,946 --> 01:20:59,279
[both yelling]

1445
01:21:00,214 --> 01:21:02,516
[both grunting]

1446
01:21:08,555 --> 01:21:11,525
The Echidna's
taking no prisoners today!

1447
01:21:11,659 --> 01:21:15,696
Sonic has heart,
but will he lose
the quill to live?

1448
01:21:17,132 --> 01:21:21,301
I don't want to fight you,
but you're not giving me
much choice.

1449
01:21:23,303 --> 01:21:26,340
[grunting]

1450
01:21:26,473 --> 01:21:30,678
[grunts]
Too easy. Let's do this.

1451
01:21:36,151 --> 01:21:37,584
Huh?

1452
01:21:37,718 --> 01:21:38,853
[grunts]

1453
01:21:47,327 --> 01:21:50,197
[both grunting]

1454
01:21:54,768 --> 01:21:55,769
[yelling]

1455
01:21:55,904 --> 01:21:57,438
[grunting]

1456
01:21:57,571 --> 01:22:02,043
Why don't you stand still
and die with honor?

1457
01:22:02,177 --> 01:22:03,310
Let me think about it.

1458
01:22:03,444 --> 01:22:07,115
Okay, I thought about it
and I pass.

1459
01:22:07,247 --> 01:22:08,950
[yelling]

1460
01:22:16,557 --> 01:22:18,325
Hi there, beautiful.

1461
01:22:19,359 --> 01:22:21,896
You're the real deal,
aren't you?

1462
01:22:22,030 --> 01:22:25,666
[speaking Italian]

1463
01:22:26,801 --> 01:22:29,204
[groaning]

1464
01:22:29,336 --> 01:22:31,806
Say goodbye, hedgehog.

1465
01:22:31,940 --> 01:22:33,440
[gasps]

1466
01:22:35,076 --> 01:22:38,146
Knuckles, stop.
Robotnik's stealing the Emerald!

1467
01:22:38,278 --> 01:22:40,781
What kind of fool
do you take me for?

1468
01:22:40,915 --> 01:22:42,349
Just look.

1469
01:22:44,752 --> 01:22:46,253
Mine.

1470
01:22:47,222 --> 01:22:49,924
Wait! That wasn't the deal.

1471
01:22:50,058 --> 01:22:51,492
[boulder thuds]

1472
01:22:52,127 --> 01:22:55,930
Oh, you poor, naive creature.

1473
01:22:56,064 --> 01:22:57,798
It's not your fault.

1474
01:22:57,932 --> 01:23:01,169
A more advanced intellect
would have seen this move
coming a mile away.

1475
01:23:01,301 --> 01:23:03,437
Or 1.6 kilometers.

1476
01:23:03,570 --> 01:23:06,306
But I trusted you!
You were my friend!

1477
01:23:06,440 --> 01:23:09,811
[cackling]

1478
01:23:13,347 --> 01:23:16,617
I'm sorry.
That just hit me funny.

1479
01:23:16,750 --> 01:23:19,286
Let this be
my final lesson to you,

1480
01:23:19,419 --> 01:23:22,023
you dim-witted
celestial skin tag.

1481
01:23:22,957 --> 01:23:24,025
Friends...

1482
01:23:24,159 --> 01:23:28,096
are open, honest
and vulnerable with each other.

1483
01:23:28,229 --> 01:23:30,764
Which means X squared
times the hypotenuse
of Y squared,

1484
01:23:30,899 --> 01:23:34,235
divided by the absolute value
of friendship, equals...

1485
01:23:34,368 --> 01:23:35,335
dookie!

1486
01:23:35,469 --> 01:23:36,905
Oh, no.

1487
01:23:41,675 --> 01:23:43,077
[Sonic, Knuckles scream]

1488
01:23:44,979 --> 01:23:49,851
Chaos is power!

1489
01:23:49,984 --> 01:23:52,020
[yelling]

1490
01:24:08,236 --> 01:24:09,971
Let's get out of here!

1491
01:24:10,104 --> 01:24:11,605
[gasps]

1492
01:24:22,482 --> 01:24:23,852
Knuckles!

1493
01:24:28,189 --> 01:24:31,125
Water again? Come on!

1494
01:24:41,069 --> 01:24:42,736
[straining]

1495
01:24:47,175 --> 01:24:48,442
[Sonic growls]

1496
01:24:48,575 --> 01:24:50,777
[straining]

1497
01:24:50,912 --> 01:24:53,047
Mmm?
[grunts]

1498
01:24:53,181 --> 01:24:55,016
[muffled exclaiming]
Mmm?

1499
01:24:55,149 --> 01:24:56,885
Mmm. Mmm.

1500
01:24:57,919 --> 01:24:59,087
Mmm?

1501
01:25:02,689 --> 01:25:06,127
[muffled yelling]

1502
01:25:07,262 --> 01:25:09,130
[Sonic grunting]

1503
01:25:09,964 --> 01:25:12,967
[muffled grunting]

1504
01:25:17,105 --> 01:25:18,973
[groaning]

1505
01:25:27,148 --> 01:25:29,549
[coughing]

1506
01:25:29,683 --> 01:25:30,919
You saved me.

1507
01:25:31,052 --> 01:25:33,821
Don't talk to me.
I'm not in the mood.

1508
01:25:33,955 --> 01:25:34,956
[grunts]

1509
01:25:35,089 --> 01:25:38,792
How dare you attack me
in my hour of sorrow!

1510
01:25:38,927 --> 01:25:39,994
[grunts]

1511
01:25:40,128 --> 01:25:41,728
Why did you save me?

1512
01:25:42,462 --> 01:25:43,398
[grunts]

1513
01:25:43,530 --> 01:25:45,133
Because you saved me first,

1514
01:25:45,266 --> 01:25:48,937
which clearly gave you
a tactical advantage
I do not understand.

1515
01:25:49,070 --> 01:25:52,907
It wasn't a tactic.
I couldn't just let you die.

1516
01:25:53,041 --> 01:25:54,909
Why?

1517
01:25:55,043 --> 01:25:58,313
I've been trying
to destroy you
since the moment we met.

1518
01:25:58,445 --> 01:26:02,317
Because being a hero
isn't about taking care
of yourself.

1519
01:26:02,449 --> 01:26:06,220
It's about taking responsibility
for other people.

1520
01:26:07,255 --> 01:26:11,558
Hmm. Wise words.
An ancient Earth proverb?

1521
01:26:11,692 --> 01:26:13,962
No, sir, that's
a Wachowski family special.

1522
01:26:14,095 --> 01:26:16,763
I got it from a guy
in a rowboat.

1523
01:26:16,898 --> 01:26:18,433
Someone who means a lot to me.

1524
01:26:18,565 --> 01:26:20,301
[biplane approaching]

1525
01:26:20,435 --> 01:26:22,136
Wait a second.
What's that sound?

1526
01:26:24,038 --> 01:26:27,574
Only Sonic the Hedgehog
needs rescuing this much.

1527
01:26:27,708 --> 01:26:30,912
[laughs]
That sly little fox!

1528
01:26:33,114 --> 01:26:36,117
Come on, Knucklehead.
We're not beat yet.

1529
01:26:36,250 --> 01:26:38,987
On the mountain,
you told me
you'd lost everything.

1530
01:26:39,120 --> 01:26:40,888
The way I did.

1531
01:26:41,022 --> 01:26:43,992
But you seem
so hopeful and free.

1532
01:26:44,125 --> 01:26:48,429
How did you move forward
despite failing again?

1533
01:26:48,562 --> 01:26:52,133
And again. And again.
And again. And again.

1534
01:26:52,266 --> 01:26:55,903
Okay, I didn't fail that much.
But I didn't do this all alone.

1535
01:26:56,037 --> 01:26:58,638
I found a new family.
New friends.

1536
01:26:58,772 --> 01:27:00,540
And you can too.

1537
01:27:02,542 --> 01:27:05,113
You don't have to be
alone anymore.

1538
01:27:07,982 --> 01:27:09,984
[bones cracking]
[Sonic] Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow!

1539
01:27:10,118 --> 01:27:13,021
Are you kidding me
with that handshake?

1540
01:27:14,788 --> 01:27:16,991
[Wade] I'm done
playing games, pal.

1541
01:27:17,859 --> 01:27:19,894
You're gonna tell me
what I want to know.

1542
01:27:21,996 --> 01:27:25,732
And I am asking you
for the last time...

1543
01:27:27,768 --> 01:27:30,071
what would you like
on your bagel?

1544
01:27:30,204 --> 01:27:32,273
I'm not telling you
anything.

1545
01:27:32,407 --> 01:27:35,076
And that is a display bagel.

1546
01:27:35,209 --> 01:27:38,513
I don't get it with you!
I mean, I've tried everything.

1547
01:27:38,645 --> 01:27:40,014
I was good cop.
I was bad cop.

1548
01:27:40,148 --> 01:27:42,283
I was cop
who offers you a bagel.

1549
01:27:42,417 --> 01:27:43,484
And nothing.
It's like--

1550
01:27:43,617 --> 01:27:45,619
That is a display bagel.
Wow.

1551
01:27:45,752 --> 01:27:47,288
[rumbling]

1552
01:27:47,422 --> 01:27:50,557
[electronic warbling]

1553
01:27:51,292 --> 01:27:52,692
[yells]

1554
01:27:54,929 --> 01:27:56,931
Doctor, you're here.

1555
01:27:58,499 --> 01:28:03,670
[in electronic voice]
Yes, I'm here,
and yet I'm...

1556
01:28:05,073 --> 01:28:06,541
not all there.

1557
01:28:06,673 --> 01:28:08,209
Sir, are you feeling okay?

1558
01:28:08,342 --> 01:28:13,014
I'm more than okay.

1559
01:28:13,147 --> 01:28:16,184
I'm upgraded.

1560
01:28:16,317 --> 01:28:19,287
[singsongy] Sinister 3.0.

1561
01:28:19,420 --> 01:28:23,224
My game is next level.

1562
01:28:23,357 --> 01:28:27,128
[warped vocalizing]

1563
01:28:28,496 --> 01:28:29,864
Hi.
[screams]

1564
01:28:32,300 --> 01:28:38,573
I can smell the electricity
in your brain.

1565
01:28:38,705 --> 01:28:40,374
[sniffs]

1566
01:28:40,508 --> 01:28:42,977
You smell like
a snack plate.

1567
01:28:44,078 --> 01:28:47,681
Yeah, no, that's fair.
I had a couple today.

1568
01:28:47,815 --> 01:28:49,616
Sit down.

1569
01:28:54,122 --> 01:28:55,689
In the chair.

1570
01:28:58,625 --> 01:29:00,495
I didn't know.

1571
01:29:00,660 --> 01:29:03,831
'Cause he was in the chair,
so I didn't-- Okay.

1572
01:29:03,965 --> 01:29:06,134
Sir? We have a problem.

1573
01:29:11,638 --> 01:29:14,741
[soldier 1]
All teams in position!
[soldier] Set up a perimeter!

1574
01:29:14,876 --> 01:29:16,743
[soldier] Move! Move! Move!

1575
01:29:31,626 --> 01:29:35,363
<i>Incorrectus,</i>
my trusty barnacle.

1576
01:29:36,597 --> 01:29:39,200
After all these years,

1577
01:29:39,699 --> 01:29:41,701
what I finally got...

1578
01:29:42,603 --> 01:29:44,872
is a solution.

1579
01:29:55,149 --> 01:29:56,783
Commander.
Status report.

1580
01:29:56,918 --> 01:30:00,421
Robotnik is in there
with Stone and a hostage.
Possibly local PD.

1581
01:30:00,555 --> 01:30:03,925
I'm not saying he's dumb,
but if he is local PD,

1582
01:30:04,058 --> 01:30:06,427
this town's
in a lot of trouble.

1583
01:30:06,561 --> 01:30:08,029
[both] Wade.

1584
01:30:19,407 --> 01:30:21,108
Um...

1585
01:30:22,310 --> 01:30:23,878
Okay.

1586
01:30:24,011 --> 01:30:26,647
Rockin' that new
spring collection, I see.

1587
01:30:26,780 --> 01:30:31,352
Well, if it isn't
the Pastry King.

1588
01:30:31,485 --> 01:30:32,853
The Donut Lord.

1589
01:30:32,987 --> 01:30:34,754
A real genius would remember
the name of the guy

1590
01:30:34,889 --> 01:30:36,557
who helped kick your butt
off this planet.

1591
01:30:36,691 --> 01:30:38,593
And I'll do it again
if you mess with Green Hills.

1592
01:30:38,725 --> 01:30:43,497
Congratulations
on your oh-so-temporary
sense of superiority.

1593
01:30:43,631 --> 01:30:46,033
You're finished, Robotnik!
We've taken everything.

1594
01:30:46,167 --> 01:30:48,669
Your lab, your drones,
your funding!

1595
01:30:48,803 --> 01:30:52,373
Let's see how big of a man
you are without
your silly little robots.

1596
01:30:53,941 --> 01:30:56,110
Would you like to see how...

1597
01:30:57,445 --> 01:30:59,779
big a man I can be?

1598
01:31:10,458 --> 01:31:13,828
Welcome to the new norm.

1599
01:31:23,838 --> 01:31:25,373
My God!

1600
01:31:28,743 --> 01:31:32,546
Doctor! Take me with you!

1601
01:31:34,448 --> 01:31:37,151
[screaming]

1602
01:31:43,090 --> 01:31:45,026
[train horn blowing]

1603
01:31:56,871 --> 01:31:59,607
He's taking everything apart.

1604
01:31:59,740 --> 01:32:01,309
He's building something.

1605
01:32:09,083 --> 01:32:11,319
[Tails]
That can only be one thing.

1606
01:32:11,452 --> 01:32:13,888
The fearsome power
of the Emerald.

1607
01:32:14,021 --> 01:32:16,324
If that thing really
turns thoughts into power,

1608
01:32:16,457 --> 01:32:18,059
we are in big trouble.

1609
01:32:18,192 --> 01:32:20,061
Robotnik has a lot
of bad thoughts.

1610
01:32:20,194 --> 01:32:23,097
Hey, Sonic, are you sure
it was a good idea

1611
01:32:23,230 --> 01:32:24,899
bringing
you-know-who aboard?

1612
01:32:25,032 --> 01:32:28,636
Knuckles isn't really a bad guy.
He's just a little mixed up.

1613
01:32:28,769 --> 01:32:30,271
I am not mixed up!

1614
01:32:30,404 --> 01:32:33,708
I have steely focus.
And I'm complex.

1615
01:32:33,841 --> 01:32:35,443
And that's a lot
for some people.

1616
01:32:35,576 --> 01:32:38,814
[chuckles]
Hope you're not still mad
I hit you with that car.

1617
01:32:38,946 --> 01:32:41,215
Pfft!
I was completely uninjured.

1618
01:32:41,349 --> 01:32:45,019
And my revenge will come
when you least expect it, fox.

1619
01:33:11,245 --> 01:33:12,480
Whoa.

1620
01:33:16,050 --> 01:33:18,652
Sir, you're magnificent!

1621
01:33:18,786 --> 01:33:20,755
Thank you, sycophant.

1622
01:33:20,888 --> 01:33:23,457
Your admiration is inevitable.

1623
01:33:33,467 --> 01:33:34,769
I knew it!

1624
01:33:34,902 --> 01:33:37,538
Just like the Stay Puft
Marshmallow Man.

1625
01:33:38,372 --> 01:33:40,541
World Domination playlist.

1626
01:33:40,674 --> 01:33:43,277
[heavy metal playing]

1627
01:33:53,889 --> 01:33:55,256
Fall back.

1628
01:33:56,357 --> 01:33:59,460
Fall back! Quick!
Retreat!

1629
01:34:01,228 --> 01:34:03,431
How are we supposed
to beat this thing?

1630
01:34:03,564 --> 01:34:04,365
We need a plan.

1631
01:34:04,498 --> 01:34:07,034
Knuckles,
use your strength to--

1632
01:34:07,168 --> 01:34:09,370
Jump off the plane. Wow.

1633
01:34:09,503 --> 01:34:13,574
Okay, this is what
we're gonna do.
Step 1: Light taunting.

1634
01:34:13,707 --> 01:34:15,543
Step 2: I have no idea.

1635
01:34:18,612 --> 01:34:19,980
Sonic!

1636
01:34:22,884 --> 01:34:24,585
[Sonic]
Nice action figure, Eggman.

1637
01:34:24,718 --> 01:34:28,088
Does it do anything
or just stand there
looking ugly?

1638
01:34:31,392 --> 01:34:34,795
Like a blister,
he keeps coming back!

1639
01:34:34,930 --> 01:34:37,833
He's on the okay-to-kill list.
Shoot the missiles.
Make a decision.

1640
01:34:37,965 --> 01:34:40,936
I need a moment, sir.
I'm trying to figure out
how to do this.

1641
01:34:41,068 --> 01:34:43,070
Did you even glance
at a manual?

1642
01:34:43,204 --> 01:34:45,473
No!
I'll do it.

1643
01:34:45,606 --> 01:34:46,674
Pardon my lightning.

1644
01:34:46,808 --> 01:34:49,143
You might want
to ground yourself.
[groaning]

1645
01:34:50,611 --> 01:34:52,046
Uh-oh.

1646
01:34:52,179 --> 01:34:55,951
I'm gonna pop that thing open
like a can of chili--
[screams]

1647
01:34:56,083 --> 01:34:57,051
[Sonic] Whoa!

1648
01:34:57,184 --> 01:34:58,986
[Tails] Hang on!

1649
01:35:00,721 --> 01:35:02,590
Whoa!

1650
01:35:02,723 --> 01:35:04,391
[grunting]

1651
01:35:04,992 --> 01:35:07,394
Whoa! [laughs]

1652
01:35:10,064 --> 01:35:11,298
Whoo!
Whoo-hoo!

1653
01:35:11,432 --> 01:35:14,034
Oh, yeah!
Whoo! Whoo-hoo-hoo!
Close one.

1654
01:35:14,168 --> 01:35:16,337
[Sonic grunts]
Sonic!

1655
01:35:19,908 --> 01:35:21,609
Robotnik!

1656
01:35:23,077 --> 01:35:24,612
Deceiver!

1657
01:35:24,745 --> 01:35:26,580
Die, mosquito.

1658
01:35:28,649 --> 01:35:29,650
[panting]

1659
01:35:29,783 --> 01:35:31,151
[grunting]

1660
01:35:35,991 --> 01:35:37,893
[yells]

1661
01:35:38,025 --> 01:35:40,127
Ooh! I felt that.

1662
01:35:46,935 --> 01:35:50,204
[growling]

1663
01:35:52,606 --> 01:35:55,276
Oh! Whoa!

1664
01:35:59,046 --> 01:36:00,414
What just happened?

1665
01:36:00,548 --> 01:36:04,118
It's the Stache Masher.
Right here in the manual.

1666
01:36:06,120 --> 01:36:08,622
Return to sender.

1667
01:36:09,858 --> 01:36:12,159
[Robotnik, Stone grunt]

1668
01:36:15,964 --> 01:36:17,298
Stone?

1669
01:36:18,198 --> 01:36:20,035
Oh, great.

1670
01:36:20,167 --> 01:36:23,304
Next thing you know,
there'll be a report about
a hostile work environment.

1671
01:36:25,941 --> 01:36:29,010
Those were our best attacks,
and they did nothing!

1672
01:36:29,143 --> 01:36:31,745
We can't beat Robotnik
as long as he's got
that Emerald.

1673
01:36:31,880 --> 01:36:33,380
He's too powerful.

1674
01:36:33,514 --> 01:36:36,283
Look, we aren't strong enough
to beat Robotnik on our own.

1675
01:36:36,417 --> 01:36:37,551
But there's three of us.

1676
01:36:37,685 --> 01:36:40,956
Your strength, your smarts
and my speed.

1677
01:36:41,088 --> 01:36:42,556
Together.
That's how we win.

1678
01:36:42,690 --> 01:36:47,394
So we make our stand here
on the field of battle.

1679
01:36:47,528 --> 01:36:48,762
As a team.

1680
01:36:48,897 --> 01:36:50,531
This is it.

1681
01:36:51,799 --> 01:36:54,568
This is our moment.

1682
01:36:56,370 --> 01:36:58,205
Time to fight.

1683
01:37:05,179 --> 01:37:09,149
Bad time to say this,
but I don't actually
have a plan.

1684
01:37:09,918 --> 01:37:11,518
Tails, any ideas?

1685
01:37:11,652 --> 01:37:13,320
We have to find
his weak spot.

1686
01:37:13,454 --> 01:37:15,090
I suggest the groin.

1687
01:37:15,222 --> 01:37:17,224
What? No. No!

1688
01:37:17,358 --> 01:37:19,961
Traditionally, yes,
the groin is the weakest spot.

1689
01:37:20,095 --> 01:37:22,063
Stop saying "groin."

1690
01:37:22,229 --> 01:37:23,965
[Robotnik] Hedgehog!

1691
01:37:24,099 --> 01:37:25,599
Look out!

1692
01:37:28,003 --> 01:37:30,738
I know what
his weak spot is.
It's me.

1693
01:37:30,872 --> 01:37:32,706
I'm the groin!

1694
01:37:33,374 --> 01:37:35,043
[Knuckles grunts]

1695
01:37:35,175 --> 01:37:36,343
Think about it.
Whoa!

1696
01:37:36,477 --> 01:37:38,079
I live rent-free
in this dude's head.

1697
01:37:38,212 --> 01:37:39,814
So if I go out there
and rile him up...

1698
01:37:39,948 --> 01:37:42,416
He'll focus on only you,
leaving himself open

1699
01:37:42,549 --> 01:37:44,685
to a flanking maneuver
from me and the fox!

1700
01:37:44,819 --> 01:37:47,554
Hedgehog,
you are a brave
and noble warrior.

1701
01:37:47,688 --> 01:37:50,357
Go to your certain death
with honor.

1702
01:37:50,491 --> 01:37:52,559
We're gonna have to work
on your pep talks, pal.

1703
01:37:52,693 --> 01:37:55,262
[laughs] Yeah.
Let's go.

1704
01:37:58,799 --> 01:38:00,234
All right, mustache.

1705
01:38:00,367 --> 01:38:03,170
You want me?
Come and get me.

1706
01:38:03,303 --> 01:38:05,840
You don't tell me
about coming and getting.

1707
01:38:05,974 --> 01:38:08,609
I am on the cutting edge
of coming and getting!

1708
01:38:08,742 --> 01:38:10,411
Coming, getting.

1709
01:38:10,544 --> 01:38:14,916
Coming, getting.
Coming, getting.
Coming, getting.

1710
01:38:17,351 --> 01:38:19,154
Oh, you're really heavy.

1711
01:38:19,286 --> 01:38:23,590
That's because I am
one million percent muscle.
Faster, fox!

1712
01:38:25,325 --> 01:38:28,796
Go! Move, guys! Move back!
Let's go, that's it!
Go, go, go!

1713
01:38:28,930 --> 01:38:29,898
Keep going!
Go! Go!

1714
01:38:30,031 --> 01:38:31,833
No, no! Stop!
Stop the truck!

1715
01:38:31,966 --> 01:38:33,467
Tom,
what happened here?

1716
01:38:33,600 --> 01:38:36,137
You thinking what
I'm thinking?
Let's get our kid.

1717
01:38:36,270 --> 01:38:37,806
[both] We need your truck!

1718
01:38:43,744 --> 01:38:46,981
[voice slowing]
Coming, getting.
Whew!

1719
01:38:47,115 --> 01:38:48,716
[Sonic] Yoo-hoo!

1720
01:38:48,850 --> 01:38:50,551
So what's
the plan here?
[panting]

1721
01:38:50,684 --> 01:38:51,518
Huh?

1722
01:38:51,652 --> 01:38:53,387
You gonna build
a big robot house?

1723
01:38:53,520 --> 01:38:55,824
Get yourself
a big robot wife?

1724
01:38:55,957 --> 01:39:00,360
I'm going to enslave humanity
and force them
to service my machines.

1725
01:39:00,494 --> 01:39:03,297
First, Green Hills.
Then the universe.

1726
01:39:03,430 --> 01:39:04,665
Then the multiverse.

1727
01:39:04,798 --> 01:39:07,668
Then who knows?
Maybe that'll be enough.

1728
01:39:07,802 --> 01:39:09,670
Full disclosure?

1729
01:39:10,337 --> 01:39:13,240
You won't be there.

1730
01:39:17,444 --> 01:39:19,780
[grunts]
Eye lasers? Really?

1731
01:39:28,223 --> 01:39:30,290
[panting]

1732
01:39:32,127 --> 01:39:34,328
Snot rocket!

1733
01:39:35,763 --> 01:39:36,831
No, no, no!

1734
01:39:38,233 --> 01:39:40,400
[screaming]

1735
01:39:42,070 --> 01:39:43,204
[grunts]

1736
01:39:43,337 --> 01:39:46,340
[laughing]
Giving up already?

1737
01:39:46,473 --> 01:39:50,677
Not so tough
when you're fighting someone
700 times your size, are ya?

1738
01:39:52,546 --> 01:39:55,049
You can't beat me!

1739
01:39:55,183 --> 01:39:58,585
I'm all-powerful!
All-knowing!

1740
01:40:01,122 --> 01:40:03,524
All-seeing.

1741
01:40:04,391 --> 01:40:06,593
Looks like your fancy robot
has a glitch.

1742
01:40:06,727 --> 01:40:08,830
[voice multiplying] Is it me?
What about me? I'm over here.

1743
01:40:08,963 --> 01:40:10,798
Up top! Down below!
Behind you! [laughs]

1744
01:40:10,932 --> 01:40:13,001
[voices overlapping]
I'm over here.
Sorry! Over here.

1745
01:40:13,134 --> 01:40:14,668
Too slow! Try again.

1746
01:40:14,803 --> 01:40:16,971
You can't outsmart me.
Missed me again.

1747
01:40:17,105 --> 01:40:18,106
I'm the outsmarter-er!

1748
01:40:18,239 --> 01:40:19,207
[grunts]

1749
01:40:19,339 --> 01:40:21,575
[yelping]

1750
01:40:23,011 --> 01:40:26,114
I didn't outsmart you.
I'm just the distraction.

1751
01:40:26,247 --> 01:40:28,049
[Knuckles] Robotnik!

1752
01:40:28,183 --> 01:40:30,919
I am also a hologram.

1753
01:40:31,052 --> 01:40:32,921
Disloyal.

1754
01:40:33,054 --> 01:40:35,957
"Dis" is how I roll.

1755
01:40:37,025 --> 01:40:38,425
[yells]

1756
01:40:38,559 --> 01:40:40,427
[Robotnik groaning]

1757
01:40:49,904 --> 01:40:52,706
[both screaming]

1758
01:40:56,110 --> 01:40:58,012
[both grunting]

1759
01:41:00,380 --> 01:41:03,051
[gasping]

1760
01:41:04,252 --> 01:41:05,920
Where's my Emerald?

1761
01:41:06,520 --> 01:41:08,323
No, no, no, no!

1762
01:41:08,455 --> 01:41:10,959
Computer, auxiliary power.

1763
01:41:14,761 --> 01:41:16,496
[groans]

1764
01:41:18,266 --> 01:41:19,868
[gasps] Oh.

1765
01:41:20,001 --> 01:41:22,904
The Emerald.
It's right there.

1766
01:41:23,037 --> 01:41:25,006
Move, you hunk of junk!

1767
01:41:29,409 --> 01:41:32,947
I have to... [groans]
...reach it.

1768
01:41:33,882 --> 01:41:35,616
[groaning]

1769
01:41:38,219 --> 01:41:39,653
[grunts]

1770
01:41:56,104 --> 01:41:57,138
Come on.

1771
01:41:59,240 --> 01:42:01,608
There he is!
Go! Go, go, go!

1772
01:42:07,982 --> 01:42:09,583
[Maddie yelling]

1773
01:42:10,318 --> 01:42:11,286
No!

1774
01:42:11,418 --> 01:42:12,887
We got you, Sonic.

1775
01:42:14,022 --> 01:42:15,589
Hold on!

1776
01:42:23,998 --> 01:42:26,667
[all panting]

1777
01:42:28,535 --> 01:42:30,972
You guys okay?
[Tom grunts] Yeah.

1778
01:42:32,340 --> 01:42:34,075
Okay.

1779
01:42:38,813 --> 01:42:40,781
I got the Emerald.
We could still defeat him.

1780
01:42:40,915 --> 01:42:44,185
Come on, come on.
How does this thing work?
What do I do?

1781
01:42:44,319 --> 01:42:45,286
[cracking]

1782
01:42:45,420 --> 01:42:47,155
What?

1783
01:42:47,288 --> 01:42:50,091
No. No, no, no!

1784
01:42:53,760 --> 01:42:58,132
Look at the happy little family.

1785
01:43:03,805 --> 01:43:06,341
You have to
get away from me.
I'm the one he wants.

1786
01:43:06,473 --> 01:43:07,741
Hey.

1787
01:43:07,875 --> 01:43:09,509
We're not going anywhere.

1788
01:43:09,643 --> 01:43:11,611
We're family.

1789
01:43:14,849 --> 01:43:16,818
And families
stick together...

1790
01:43:19,486 --> 01:43:20,888
no matter what.

1791
01:43:23,757 --> 01:43:25,093
I love you guys.

1792
01:43:25,792 --> 01:43:27,362
We love you too,
Sonic.

1793
01:43:27,494 --> 01:43:29,864
[chaos emeralds chiming]

1794
01:43:36,037 --> 01:43:37,637
No!

1795
01:43:39,440 --> 01:43:41,508
I got him!

1796
01:43:41,641 --> 01:43:47,448
I finally got him!
[cackles]

1797
01:43:47,581 --> 01:43:49,549
[thudding]

1798
01:43:50,684 --> 01:43:52,719
What was that?

1799
01:44:21,249 --> 01:44:23,051
[gasps]

1800
01:44:25,453 --> 01:44:26,954
[yelps]

1801
01:44:32,260 --> 01:44:35,562
[panting]

1802
01:44:38,399 --> 01:44:40,301
It's over, Eggman.

1803
01:44:40,435 --> 01:44:44,972
[chuckles]
I like the new look.
It works for you.

1804
01:44:45,106 --> 01:44:48,042
What do you say
we just let bygones be bygones?

1805
01:44:48,176 --> 01:44:50,011
I did some things,
you did some things.

1806
01:44:50,144 --> 01:44:52,213
There are good people
on both sides.

1807
01:44:53,747 --> 01:44:57,051
Surely two intelligent beings

1808
01:44:58,618 --> 01:45:00,855
can work these things out!

1809
01:45:07,761 --> 01:45:09,629
[grunts]

1810
01:45:12,632 --> 01:45:13,600
Come on, buddy.

1811
01:45:13,733 --> 01:45:15,136
Get him, Sonic!
Come on.

1812
01:45:15,269 --> 01:45:16,770
Yeah. Come on.

1813
01:45:20,541 --> 01:45:22,176
[gasping]

1814
01:45:32,987 --> 01:45:34,788
It's like that?

1815
01:45:35,957 --> 01:45:38,625
Okay, we're not friends.

1816
01:45:42,762 --> 01:45:45,199
Later, hater!

1817
01:45:56,477 --> 01:45:58,379
Sonic!
Buddy! [laughs]

1818
01:45:58,513 --> 01:46:00,281
Wait!
You cannot touch him!

1819
01:46:00,414 --> 01:46:03,084
The hedgehog holds
the power of the Emerald.

1820
01:46:03,217 --> 01:46:07,822
I am sorry.
He is no longer
the Sonic you once knew.

1821
01:46:08,256 --> 01:46:09,290
What?

1822
01:46:24,472 --> 01:46:26,407
[sniffs]

1823
01:46:27,674 --> 01:46:28,809
Mmm.

1824
01:46:28,943 --> 01:46:30,945
Oh, you got to try this.

1825
01:46:36,317 --> 01:46:40,021
Okay. He is exactly
the Sonic you once knew.

1826
01:46:41,688 --> 01:46:43,224
Uh-huh.
Uh-huh.

1827
01:46:51,566 --> 01:46:53,301
Sonic!
Whoa!

1828
01:46:54,869 --> 01:46:56,770
Bring it in, bud.

1829
01:46:57,905 --> 01:46:59,607
It's good to be back
in blue.

1830
01:46:59,739 --> 01:47:03,344
The golden god thing was fun,
but blue has always been
more my color.

1831
01:47:03,477 --> 01:47:04,579
Looks good on you.

1832
01:47:04,711 --> 01:47:07,148
Sonic, you were
the most powerful hero

1833
01:47:07,281 --> 01:47:10,084
in the universe,
and you let it go.

1834
01:47:10,218 --> 01:47:11,319
Why?

1835
01:47:12,887 --> 01:47:16,224
Because I still have
some growing up to do.

1836
01:47:18,192 --> 01:47:20,561
And I kind of like
being a kid.

1837
01:47:20,695 --> 01:47:22,530
And you're not
just any kid.

1838
01:47:22,663 --> 01:47:24,498
You're our kid.

1839
01:47:24,632 --> 01:47:25,900
That's right.

1840
01:47:26,033 --> 01:47:28,536
Bring it in!
[Tails] Yay. Hugs.

1841
01:47:28,669 --> 01:47:31,973
It's a good thing
we didn't do this before.
You would've blown up.

1842
01:47:39,247 --> 01:47:40,848
[Sonic] Whoa! You fixed it.

1843
01:47:40,982 --> 01:47:44,385
I've spent my whole life
questing for this.

1844
01:47:44,518 --> 01:47:45,686
Now I have it.

1845
01:47:45,820 --> 01:47:47,588
Now we have it.

1846
01:47:47,722 --> 01:47:50,124
What do we do with it?
What next?

1847
01:47:50,258 --> 01:47:52,293
There were once
two orders of heroes

1848
01:47:52,426 --> 01:47:56,464
who protected the galaxy
from those who would use
the Emerald for evil.

1849
01:47:56,597 --> 01:48:00,635
But they have all passed on
to the great battleground
in the sky.

1850
01:48:00,767 --> 01:48:04,272
So we start a new order.
The three of us.

1851
01:48:04,405 --> 01:48:05,772
This is no light task.

1852
01:48:05,906 --> 01:48:10,945
We must make a vow
to use our powers
to keep the universe safe,

1853
01:48:11,612 --> 01:48:13,414
to watch out for each other.

1854
01:48:13,547 --> 01:48:15,249
Our new tribe.

1855
01:48:15,383 --> 01:48:16,417
Oh, I know!

1856
01:48:16,550 --> 01:48:17,784
A power bump!

1857
01:48:17,918 --> 01:48:19,587
Good idea.

1858
01:48:19,720 --> 01:48:23,224
It's an Earth custom.
An unbreakable promise.

1859
01:48:23,357 --> 01:48:25,226
Very well.

1860
01:48:25,826 --> 01:48:28,396
A power bump it is.

1861
01:48:29,497 --> 01:48:31,265
Power bump!

1862
01:48:34,969 --> 01:48:36,704
[Sonic over PA]
It's truly a beautiful day

1863
01:48:36,837 --> 01:48:39,006
for baseball here
in Green Hills.

1864
01:48:39,140 --> 01:48:40,841
An exciting lineup today

1865
01:48:40,975 --> 01:48:44,145
with the debut appearance
of two new players!

1866
01:48:44,278 --> 01:48:48,549
On the mound,
rookie sensation
from across the galaxy,

1867
01:48:48,683 --> 01:48:51,052
Miles "Tails" Prower,

1868
01:48:51,185 --> 01:48:56,424
facing off against
the powerhouse,
Knuckles the Echidna.

1869
01:48:56,557 --> 01:48:59,160
Um, I don't understand.

1870
01:48:59,293 --> 01:49:01,562
Why am I angry
at the enemy ball?

1871
01:49:01,696 --> 01:49:02,863
You're not angry.

1872
01:49:02,997 --> 01:49:04,699
You just want to hit it
as hard as you can

1873
01:49:04,832 --> 01:49:06,033
and then run around the bases.

1874
01:49:06,167 --> 01:49:09,370
But if my quest ends
where I am standing,

1875
01:49:09,503 --> 01:49:10,905
why run at all?

1876
01:49:11,038 --> 01:49:13,974
Ugh. I can't with this guy.
Why do I even try?

1877
01:49:14,108 --> 01:49:16,777
This is just a game.
We're out here having fun.

1878
01:49:16,911 --> 01:49:18,446
Just having some fun.

1879
01:49:18,579 --> 01:49:20,948
Fun. Huh.

1880
01:49:21,082 --> 01:49:23,317
All right!
Give him the heat, Tails!

1881
01:49:23,451 --> 01:49:25,319
Hope you're ready
for my fastball.

1882
01:49:25,453 --> 01:49:27,955
Your fastball
will be dishonored.

1883
01:49:28,089 --> 01:49:30,424
And so will you, fox.
[grunts]

1884
01:49:30,558 --> 01:49:31,592
Easy, guys!

1885
01:49:31,726 --> 01:49:32,960
Don't think about it too much.

1886
01:49:33,094 --> 01:49:34,995
Just keep your elbow up,
eye on the ball

1887
01:49:35,129 --> 01:49:36,397
and give it a ride.

1888
01:49:36,530 --> 01:49:38,099
A ride? To where?

1889
01:49:38,766 --> 01:49:39,700
[grunts]

1890
01:49:39,835 --> 01:49:41,302
[growls]

1891
01:49:42,069 --> 01:49:43,537
Power bump!

1892
01:49:45,740 --> 01:49:47,274
[screams]

1893
01:49:47,875 --> 01:49:50,044
Ha! Victory is mine!

1894
01:49:50,177 --> 01:49:52,747
Hey, no fair!
That shouldn't count.

1895
01:49:52,880 --> 01:49:55,015
First base
is also mine!

1896
01:49:55,149 --> 01:49:56,852
I think that was
our only ball.
[laughs]

1897
01:49:56,984 --> 01:49:59,754
I have conquered
the second of the bases!

1898
01:49:59,887 --> 01:50:01,255
Who wants ice cream?

1899
01:50:01,389 --> 01:50:02,690
Knocked the cover off that.

1900
01:50:02,824 --> 01:50:05,126
Ice cream!
Ice cream, yeah!

1901
01:50:05,259 --> 01:50:09,263
[laughing]
I am having the fun!
What is ice cream?

1902
01:50:09,397 --> 01:50:12,600
It's a dessert.
If you like fun,
you're gonna love it.

1903
01:50:12,733 --> 01:50:16,003
Oh, yum. Dessert.
Does it have grapes in it?

1904
01:50:16,137 --> 01:50:17,738
No, not usually.

1905
01:50:17,873 --> 01:50:20,174
I'm proud of
our little guy.

1906
01:50:20,307 --> 01:50:23,812
I really like
his new friends,
especially the red one.

1907
01:50:23,944 --> 01:50:26,580
He cracks me up.
Heck of a swing too.

1908
01:50:26,714 --> 01:50:27,849
Come on, fox.

1909
01:50:27,982 --> 01:50:29,617
Our dessert adventure
awaits.
Whoo!

1910
01:50:29,750 --> 01:50:30,785
Good job,
guys.
Yeah.

1911
01:50:30,918 --> 01:50:32,219
You too, baby.

1912
01:50:32,353 --> 01:50:35,156
Let's go get some ice cream.
Come on, come on.

1913
01:50:35,289 --> 01:50:37,558
I'm happy for you, pal.

1914
01:50:37,691 --> 01:50:39,093
Got your wingmen.

1915
01:50:39,226 --> 01:50:40,561
Perfect friends
to grow up with.

1916
01:50:40,694 --> 01:50:44,365
Come on, Knuckles.
Ah!
My victory chariot!

1917
01:50:46,167 --> 01:50:49,370
I've got a lot more
than that... Dad.

1918
01:50:54,708 --> 01:50:56,210
Race you to the truck.

1919
01:50:57,711 --> 01:50:58,979
One, two, three, go!

1920
01:50:59,113 --> 01:51:01,549
No, don't go easy on me.
I want your best.

1921
01:51:01,682 --> 01:51:04,585
Sonic, I have just been told
they have sprinkles.

1922
01:51:04,718 --> 01:51:08,389
Ice cream and sprinkles?
This is your new destiny.

1923
01:51:08,522 --> 01:51:13,394
What a perfect meal
to celebrate my victory
over you in base of ball.

1924
01:51:13,527 --> 01:51:16,230
What?
I mean,
you barely beat me.

1925
01:51:16,363 --> 01:51:19,600
Ha! You've never been
beaten so hard.

1926
01:51:20,802 --> 01:51:22,403
[Sonic laughs]

1927
01:51:23,905 --> 01:51:25,272
Can't forget this.

1928
01:51:26,707 --> 01:51:28,442
["Stars In The Sky" playing]

1929
